Wenn du deinen PC upgraden m√∂chtest, w√§re der RAM eine √ºberlegung wert.', "So far, it's been running great and looks very cool. Below, I will outline the pros and cons of these RAM sticks based on my personal experience:Pros:  Impressive 32GB Capacity: The inclusion of two 16GB RAM sticks has provided a substantial boost to my computer's memory capacity. Easy Installation: Installing these RAM sticks was a breeze. The sticks fit seamlessly into the RAM slots on my motherboard, and the installation process was straightforward. The user-friendly design ensures that even those with limited technical knowledge can successfully upgrade their system's memory.Cons:  Higher Price Tag: While these RAM sticks offer excellent performance and aesthetic appeal, they may not be the most budget-friendly option on the market. The advanced features, larger capacity, and eye-catching design contribute to a higher price point compared to more basic RAM options. However, the enhanced performance and visual impact may justify the investment for those seeking a high-quality and visually pleasing upgrade.In summary, the two sticks of RAM provide a substantial boost to your computer's memory capacity, allowing for smooth multitasking and seamless performance, especially for resource-intensive tasks. The stylish design and vibrant colors enhance the visual appeal of your system, particularly in an all white build. The easy installation process ensures a hassle-free upgrade experience. However, it's worth noting that these RAM sticks come with a higher price tag compared to more basic options. If you prioritize performance, aesthetics, and are willing to invest in a premium RAM upgrade, these sticks are a fantastic choice for taking your system to the next level."]

Product: CORSAIR CMSX32GX4M2A3000C18 Computer Memory, ddr4, 2 x 16GB
Reviews: ['as expected. works like a charm', 'Update on 22 Sep 20:As advised by JC in the QnA section, I contacted Amazon. And within 1 hour, received reply from Amazon on the replacement.And within 24 hours after the email from Amazon, I have received my replacement set...Unfortunately... again, 1 out of 4 stick is defective.Maybe you may question why I can confirm the 1 out of 4 is defective?The answer is because the 3 out of 4 are running good, in the same laptop (HP Probook 440 G7).Finally, Amazon give me 2 options:- full refund, or- partial refund for the defective piece of RAM.Raise the review from 3 star to 4 star because of the good support from Amazon.Speedy delivery.Install to my HP Probook 440 G7 (2 slots).There were some hiccup.Insert 2 out of 4 x16Gb into the 2 slots of my probook, but no sound no picture... really black screen at all.Named as RAM no. 46 and no.47Insert another 2 RAM (named as no.41 and no.42).Still no sound no picture..Insert back the original RAM. Boot in Win10 no problem.Troubleshoot 1:Slot 1: original RAMSlot 2: RAM no.41It takes longer time, but it manage successfully boot in Win10.Run CPUZ to check and seems ok.Running at 1333mhz (or 2666mhz), CL18.Good RAMTroubleshoot 2,3,4:Slot 1: original RAMSlot 2: RAM no. 42, 46, 47Found out that RAM 46 is defective.Troubleshoot 5:Slot 1: no.41Slot 2: no.42No picture, but this time got very loud Beep Beep Beep.Troubleshoot 6: (successful)Slot 1: no.42 (please note that i swab no.42 from slot 2 to slot 1 this time)Slot 2: no.41 (please note that i swab no.41 from slot 1 to slot 2 this time)Again, take a bit longer time, but finally manage to boot in Win10 successfully.Lastly, not sure how to contact Amazon related this issue?I don‚Äôt want to return the whole package as I bought them in really good price.Or should I contact Corsair? Thanks!', 'Tested in many laptops and Mac, so far stability is excellent and passed memtest without any issues.Highly recommended for a fuss-free SODIMM non ECC DDR4 RAM.', 'Today I received the 32GB (2x16GB) module and installed it into my ThinkPad X1 Extreme Gen 2. Product: CORSAIR CMK32GX4M2D3600C18 Vengeance LPX 32GB (2 x 16GB) DDR4 DRAM Memory Kit, Black, 32GB Kit (4 x 8GB)
Reviews: ['I have been using corsair for a long time and this model is the best one yet', 'Bought the 32GB set for my new build. Low profile heat sink certainly help with the small space that ITX case has!', 'Got a kit of 3600 C18 2x16GB RAM and the first day I used it, it BSoD and the orange DRAM light on the motherboard lit up and the system refused to post. I sent the motherboard and CPU I had, ASUS TUF B550M PLUS WIFI II & Ryzen 5 5600, back to the shop to test for problems but the motherboard and CPU worked without problems! This proved that these stick of RAM was at fault, so I am returning these.', "Ram Corsair Vengeance Lpx Ddr4-Ram 3600Mhz 2X16Gb CL18.Voglio sottolineare che una 3600MHz CL18 e una 3200MHz CL16, sono identiche, stessa latency.Non mi √® mai servito pi√π di 16GB di ram, fino a quando non ho scoperto Stable Diffusion, e la ram non mi bastava pi√π.Ho visto subito la differenza aumentandola.Un processo molto pesante su 16GB di ram impiegava 22 minuti, con i 32GB di ram s'√® ridotto a 17 minuti.La mia RTX ha solo 6GB di vram ma in qualunque caso serve la ram di sistema per far girare tutto, e solo Python se ne prende oltre 7GB.Stable Diffusion ha bisogno di 32GB, altrimenti si √® limitatissimi.La ram della Corsair √® ottima, appena installata, riconosciuta in automatico a 3600MHz.In precedenza avevo una G-Skill da 3000MHz che dovevo tenere a 2933MHz perch√® altrimenti non reggeva e mi crashava il sistema.Ricordo che la G-skill la pagai 150 in 2x8GB, ed era il prezzo pi√π vantaggioso in quel momento...La prossima mobo avr√† almeno 64GB, ma per il momento la vecchia rig va ancora ottimamente.Corsair Vengeance, ora sceglier√≤ sempre queste.", "The Corsair VENGEANCE LPX DDR4 RAM 32GB kit is a solid choice for anyone looking to upgrade their system's memory.Reliable Performance:This RAM kit does exactly what RAM is supposed to do - it provides reliable and fast memory performance. With 32GB of memory and a 3600MHz speed, it's perfect for handling multitasking and demanding applications.Easy Installation:Installing this RAM was a breeze. The design and build quality are top-notch, and it fit perfectly into my motherboard without any issues.Boosted Gaming and Performance:With this upgraded RAM, my system's overall performance has noticeably improved. Gaming sessions are smoother, and multitasking feels much more fluid.Corsair Quality Assurance:Corsair is known for producing quality computer components, and this RAM kit lives up to their reputation. It feels sturdy and dependable, giving me confidence in its long-term performance.Heat Spreader Design:The VENGEANCE LPX comes with a sleek heat spreader design that not only looks cool but also helps keep the RAM cool during heavy usage.Great Deal for the Price:Considering the performance and brand reputation, this RAM kit offers a great deal for its price. It competes well with higher-priced options without breaking the bank.Ideal for Gaming and Content Creation:If you're a gamer or content creator, this 32GB kit is an excellent investment. It provides the extra memory needed to handle resource-intensive tasks without any hiccups.Final Verdict:In conclusion, the Corsair VENGEANCE LPX DDR4 RAM 32GB (2x16GB) 3600MHz delivers solid performance and gets the job done without any fuss. If you're looking for reliable and fast RAM to boost your system's performance, this kit is a great choice. It's a dependable option for both gamers and content creators alike. When it comes to value for money, the Corsair VENGEANCE LPX DDR4 RAM 32GB kit is a winner, offering a great deal for its impressive performance. I'm pleased with my purchase, and I highly recommend it to anyone in need of an RAM upgrade.", "Petit erreur a la commande mais tres vite regl√© par amazon.Les 16go c'est bien mais les 32go sont mieux si comme moi vous avez pour habitude de regarder des video/strem sur le cot√©. √âgalement plus de ram vous permer de reduire l√©g√®rement un bottleneck cpuApres c'est du corsair RAS.", "I'm usually fairly good at picking parts and ensuring that clearance won't be an issue, however in this instance, I didn't feel comfortable with the setup.Case: NZXT H510 FlowMobo: MAG z690 Tomahawk WiFi DDR4CPU Cooler: AK620 Zero DarkOriginally I'd gone with the Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro 32GB (16x2) kit. Installing everything the tempered side panel would close, but only just. With one cpu cooler fan having to be positioned above the Vengeance stick, it made it rise a millimeter or two so closing the tempered panel made it pretty much flush, if not push a bit, that fan.Though it may have been alright like that, I didn't like it so opted instead for this kit and shaved off more than enough mm's with it so that wouldn't be the case.I should have done more research, but sometimes even with that, things don't always work. However, this ram is solid. I've used Corsair for many years as many others I'm sure and am confident it'll last as long as I have the rig.", 'La DDR4 32gb 3600 MHz √® stata presa per aumentare la vecchia RAM da 16gb che purtroppo √® andata fuori produzione. Comunque una volta montata su scheda madre Amd b550 dopo pochi secondi √® stata riconosciuta e funziona bene. Con 32gb Windows 10 √® sicuramente pi√π veloce.', "L'unico problema che ho avuto √® che una delle 2 all'inizio non ne voleva sapere di impostarsi a 3600 mhz. Cambiandole slot nella scheda madre ho risolto.", "I bought this kit to bring my existing 32GB kit up to 64GB.  It's been a year or two between purchases, but the brand and model number are the same.  That's about as close as I can get in terms of compatibility.  The manufacturers say your ram should ALL be from the same kit because even if the model numbers are the same there could be differences.  Corsair even replaced ALL my ram that was comprised of two kits once because they were so insistent that it all be from the same batch.  That one time I had to RMA ram though Corsair, they were amazingly helpful.  Personally I haven't had trouble yet mixing Corsair ram kits or singles.I have it clocked to 3600MHz (XMP).  I tested the ram with Memtest86 (Passmark) for four passes (7.5 hours) and it found no errors.These LPX kits are my favorite.  With one of the lowest profiles available (34mm) with heat spreaders, they fit right under my NH-D15 chromax cooler without even having to raise the fan.I don't understand why the product description says they are iCue Compatible.  They don't have RGB.  It's not worth mentioning iCue in relation to LPX line of products."]

Product: Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 DRAM 3200MHz (PC4-25600) C16 Memory Kit - Black
Reviews: ['Thanks seller will purchase again', "I got this for lightning deal  but also because the 3200mhz models were out of stock or had to wait for shipping and I didn‚Äôt want to waste time  .However, I should have done More research on it for  my Ryzen 5 3600 system, As ( for my case) I couldn‚Äôt get its xmp profile to work stably at Exactly Full 3000mhz  on My b450m motherboard steel legend ( it might occasionally cause bios Settings reset on boot ) and had to dial it back down to 2933mhz. Seems certain  Am4 motherboards might  prefer specific MHz values that they listed, also do note I couldn‚Äôt  not find this model of  ram on the  QVL ( qualified vendor list) on ASRock website of my motherboard , so I should  had bought it knowing the full risk it might it work exactly out of the box but at least it worked  according to speed ( at least at 2933mhz on my system ) after I  enabled  XMP and tweak settings down if needed be.In the end i had to buy another set of RAM because I realised Ryzen/AMD can be rather picky with RAM and it's better to pick a RAM that is under QVL.", 'These are the good ol Samsung B-die v4.31 and runs perfectly at 4000mhz CL16 in my MSI X570S Tomahawk Max Wifi mobo using XMP profile. Although stated as tweaked for Intel XMP, the AM4 mobo accepted it running at 4000mhz CL16 without any issues.', 'Upgraded from Corsair Vengeance LPX 8GB (2x4GB) DDR4 DRAM 2400MHz to this (Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 DRAM 3200MHz). Working well as described without fuss or big issues. Only thing I noticed is for my previous RAM, BIOS automatically reflected and run at the high freq of 2400Mhz. For this RAM, putting BIOS to auto will only be running it at 2133MHz. Will need to manually set it to run 3200MHz.', 'Make my PC get second wind!', 'Got 2x 8gb sticks a while ago that were not used for over a year...1 of the sticks stopped working or might never have worked. This one replaced it without issue', 'Runs well with 13600kno issues running at 4000mhz cl16', 'Affordable and very easy to install. Faced no clearance issue even with my bulky cpu tower cooler.', 'Bought this to double my RAM and clear my memory bottleneck. Does its job. My only comment is the delivery should have at least ring the doorbell or give me a call before leaving a $80+ item between the door and the gate.', 'I started with 2 sets of Quad-channel (4GBx4) 3000-CL15 DDR4. I moved to 8GBx2 and then to 16GB x2. All running at XMP setting and never regretted any of it (all of the same model for compatibility). I can mix different sizes per channel and no compatibility issues. The Quad-channel gives so much bandwidth that I do not need to worry about bottlenecks or using higher speed RAMs. Perhaps the next upgrade is to use higher speed ones at Quad Channel with a high 4.5ghz multi-core CPU. Right now, the performance for both games and file transfer is amazing!']

Product: CORSAIR CMK64GX4M2E3200C16 Vengeance LPX DDR4 3200(PC4-25600) C161.35V Desktop Memory Kit, Black, 64 GB
Reviews: ['Works as expected. I am not an overclocker.', 'The ram works perfectly with my ryzen 5 3600. I did not encounter any bluescreen so far.', "It's able to post and boot into the OS at 3200 mhz,  but streaming videos from Youtube, the videos will hang and stutter badly. This occurs at both XMP frequency and setting the freq manually. Had to run it at 3133 mhz for stable performance. Compared to an older pair of Crucial Ballistix, 2x16gb, the Crucial rams are able to run at 3200 mhz flawlessly.", 'This is probably one of the most popular RAM modules in the market for a reason. It performs well.I also had a requirement for my RAM to be low profile to fit my Noctua NH-D15, which this RAM does very well.RAM doesn‚Äôt need much cooling, and quite puzzled to see overgrown RAM modules which doesn‚Äôt really serve any purpose.Also I was building a professional machine and was avoiding RGB. For some RGB may mean a lot, and in that case this is not for you.Finally Amazon allowed me to purchase this at a very competitive price (I purchased 128GB for data analysis work), although my order got filled after around two months due to lack of stocks.', 'Received the Item Well and Good. Fast Delivery. Working well as expected. The price is good when compared to SG Pricing. Paired with AMD 5600X, it delivers what i need.', "Low profile RAM, no RGB. These 2 are good points. However, I didn't pay much attention to the part number prior my purchase as I checked  from Crucial showed that it is optimized for Ryzen. Therefore, setting DOCP caused the windows to have random reboot even during the windows installation (e.g: I could not even complete my initial user creation). Latest BIOS detects the DOCP profile of the RAM, but it is unstable for me.", 'Bought for new build with Intel 12th gen cpu i7-12700 and Asus TUF GAMING B660M-PLUS WIFI D4 motherboard - working excellent!', 'Great seller, Awesome, thank you so much. Love it‚Ä¶', 'Low profile, cheaper and a fast memory card', "With the price of DDR4 coming down, I decided to make the move to 64GB in my main (ITX) system. I'm glad I did.This LPX kit was a great price, went straight in and booted straight up. 3200 / C16 is not the fastest speed or the fastest timings, but having 64GB in an ITX system is great.Recommended!"]

Product: CORSAIR Vengeance LPX 64GB (2x32GB) DDR4 3600(PC4-28800) C181.35V Desktop Memory - Black
Reviews: ["Installed in a Corsair One A200 with B550 Phantom mainboard.Opened the Corsair A200, remove top fan (button on the top back), open on the left side, remove the existing sticks (2x16 3200Mhz Vengeance) and plugged in the 2x32 3600Mhz Vengeance LPX.Started the machine and entered the bios, instantly recognized the memory and was already running at 3600Mhz, which is perfect for AMD cpu's because of the speed of the infinity fabric.  Rebooted and booted into windows, have been using it now for a few days and works fine, computer runs stable and no issues. Slightly faster in compiling, project which took 2 minutes sharp now compiles in 1m50. Not a huge difference, but still a nice improvement nonetheless for the 15 euro the 3600 version cost more than the 3200 memory.", 'Die Corsair Vengeance LPX 64GB (2x32GB) DDR4 3600MHz C18 ist ein hochwertiges DDR4-Speicherkit, das sich f√ºr High-End-Gaming- und Workstation-Systeme eignet. Es bietet eine hohe Geschwindigkeit von 3600 MHz und eine niedrige Latenz von CL18, was zu hervorragenden Leistungsergebnissen f√ºhrt.Das Kit ist in einem schwarzen Heatspreader mit einem Low-Profile-Design ausgef√ºhrt, so dass es auch in kompakten Geh√§usen problemlos montiert werden kann. Es bietet eine hervorragende Leistung, Zuverl√§ssigkeit und ein gutes Preis-Leistungs-Verh√§ltnis.Hier ist eine kurze Zusammenfassung der Bewertung:  Leistung: Sehr gut  Qualit√§t: Sehr gut  Preis-Leistungs-Verh√§ltnis: Gut  Empfehlung: EmpfohlenIch hoffe, dies hilft!', "I purchased these moduals on top of the 64GB installed in my system. I wanted to go the full blown 128GB not only for gaming, but for photo/video editing. Speed and efficiency is the name of the game. I tweaked it up to a sweet spot 3800mhz. Product: Crucial CT2K32G48C40S5 DDR5-4800 SODIMM RAM Memory Kit, 32GB, 1.1V, CAS Latency 40 (Pack of 2), Black
Reviews: ['I purchased the Crucial 16GB DDR5 SODIMM RAM through Amazon in September 2022 and has start to malfunction in Feb 2023, this is made worst with the extremely disappointing experience in trying to make warranty claims.The ram no longer function properly, causing crashes and errors on my laptop. I attempted to return the product and work with both Amazon and Crucial customer service, but was met with unhelpful and slow responses. I ultimately had to waste time and money finding a solution to the issue. I would not recommend this product or the buying experience through Amazon.', 'I recently purchased a Dell XPS 15 9520 in early May and it only had 16gb but since RAM is literally one of the easiest things to install yourself I never pay extra for the "upgraded" ram from Dell or any other manufacturer and just install it myself at literally about 1/3 of the cost Dell, HP, Alienware, etc want to charge you for it.  Anyway, I build desktop PCs for folks, run a couple media servers, and have personally owned and used laptops myself since the late 90s.  Again, adding some extra ram was always an easy proposition - the worst part being prying off the bottom of the laptop and not breaking the plastic or scratching the edges etc.  Once installed, you\'d just power it back on. There would be a slightly longer delay to boot up than usual for the first boot after the upgrade but then everything would be fine. I\'ve done it countless times for laptops and desktops alike....but this Dell is different.  I did two upgrades at the same time this go \'round for my laptop. I had upgraded from a 1tb sky hynix nvme that came stock to a 990 Pro 2tb and also bumped up from 16gb ram to 64gb.  I installed both at the same time...turned the pc back on and, the Dell boot logo pops up like normal and then.....nothing....it just sits there....and sits there some more.  5 minutes pass...nothing...just a static boot logo on the screen. I assumed the cloned drive was likely the culprit and swapped back the original drive first and turned it back on...same thing...just the boot logo would pop up.  So i tried putting back in the stock ram and voila...booted normal again.  Swapped out for the 990 pro and left the stock RAM back in and once again just a static Dell boot logo for 5 minutes with no signs of anything changing so I thought the issue was definitely the RAM was incompatible for some reason and I was getting ready to return it when I started googling some more about this laptop. I already knew it\'s notorious for not taking ram from corsair or kingston for some reason but from everything I had read this Crucial ram worked fine as an upgrade.  Eventually, after getting lost in so many threads with people struggling to upgrade RAM on this laptop I came across a reddit thread with people saying even the Crucial ram was giving them issues but thankfully one person said you literally have to wait a LONG time for it to recognize the new amount of RAM.  This person said you have to let it sit on that Dell boot logo for at least 20 minutes before it will finally recognize there\'s some new RAM installed.  So I put the Crucial ram back in...booted to that static Dell logo and waited...and waited...about 25 minutes later it finally pops up with a new screen saying "the amount of memory detected has changed. press ok to continue".  I pressed ok and it restarted and went straight into the OS like normal lol.So, long story short.  it DOES work but the laptop makes it seem like it\'s not working. I\'ve NEVER seen a PC take THAT long to reconize new ram installed but this one does so if you own this lovely laptop please be advised this is normal and just let it sit there and do it\'s thing for about 25 minutes.  It\'ll work...eventually lol.  So far I haven\'t had any additional issues with slow boot times. The whole booting to OS process only takes around 7-10 seconds now like it should.  Fantastic savings over buying the Dell ram.  64gb of Dell ram is close to $500 currently. I got this 32gbx2 kit on Prime Day for $130.  MASSIVE savings. In fact I was able to get the 990 PRO 2tb nvme and this kit and STILL save almost $250 total versus just what Dell wants for the ram kit.', "Tutto bene anche se Amazon spedisce senza nessuna protezione ESD! Avrei giurato che sarebberoarrivate rotte. Per fortuna non √® stato cosi. Vorrei ricordare ad Amazon che tutto quello che √® elettronica sfusa, come componenti o parti VA SPEDITO IN UN CONTENITORE ANTISTATICO!Ad ogni modo non sono qui a scrivere di queste cavolate che fa Amazon ma per dare un prezioso aiuto aquanti vogliono installare i moduli da se anche se non hanno una competenza in merito.Ogni volta che si installa dell'hardware nuovo bisogna prima disconnettere la batteria. Poi una volta installati i moduli riconnetterla in modo che venga fatto un reset. Alla prima accensione dopo la sostituzione con la nuova RAM partir√† il POST (Power On System Test) dato che il BIOS si accorge che l'hardware √® cambiato. Per il mio PC un HP Zbook power G9 questo test richiede pi√π di 6-8 minuti durante i quali lo schermo del PC rester√† spento. Ancora di pi√π se avete cambiato altro hardware allo stesso tempo. Durante il test le ventole andranno a media velocit√†, non vi preoccupate. Aspettate con calma che il test finisca prima di pensare che i moduli siano rotti o difettosi o incompatibili con il vostro PC. Alla fine un messaggio del BIOS vi avviser√† che un componente hardware √® stato cambiato (la RAM in questo caso) e vi chieder√† di confermare premendo invio. A  questo punto il PC si riavvia come al solito. Controllate quindi che la quantit√† di RAM che il sistema vede sia quella che vi aspettate. Solo dopo, casomai, procedete al reso. In ogni caso il BIOS dara informazioni sul difetto se riscontrato anche con dei messaggi luminosi sulla tastiera (leggete il manuale di servizio del vostro PC in merito).Crucial da molte informazioni per l'installazione della RAM ed √® precisa sui moduli compatibili con il vostro hardware. Purtroppo non dice nulla sulla procedura di POST e si ritrova con resi funzionanti da persone poco esperte che alla partenza con schermo nero fermano la procedura di POST anticipatamente pensando a qualche cosa che non va.", "The Crucial RAM 64GB Kit (2x32GB) DDR5 4800MHz CL40 Laptop Memory is a high-performance memory solution that elevates your laptop's capabilities to new heights. With its impressive capacity, blazing-fast speeds, and reliable performance, this RAM kit offers a significant boost to your laptop's multitasking capabilities and overall responsiveness.One of the standout features of the Crucial RAM 64GB Kit is its substantial capacity. With two 32GB modules, this kit provides a total of 64GB of RAM, offering ample space for memory-intensive tasks such as video editing, content creation, and virtualization. The increased capacity allows for smoother multitasking and seamless operation of resource-demanding applications.The DDR5 technology employed by this RAM kit brings a significant performance improvement over previous generations. The 4800MHz speed ensures lightning-fast data transfer rates, reducing latency and improving overall system responsiveness. This is particularly beneficial for memory-intensive applications, gaming, and heavy multitasking, where fast data access is crucial.The CL40 latency rating further enhances the memory's efficiency by reducing delays in data retrieval and processing. This results in smoother system operations and improved performance, allowing for a more fluid and enjoyable user experience, even when running demanding tasks simultaneously.Crucial is a reputable brand known for its reliability and quality, and this RAM kit is no exception. The modules are rigorously tested to ensure compatibility, stability, and optimal performance. With the Crucial RAM 64GB Kit, you can have peace of mind knowing that your laptop's memory is built to withstand rigorous usage and provide reliable performance.Installing the Crucial RAM 64GB Kit is a straightforward process. The memory modules are designed to be compatible with a wide range of laptops, and Crucial provides clear instructions for hassle-free installation. The plug-and-play nature of this RAM kit means that you can quickly upgrade your laptop's memory without requiring advanced technical knowledge or specialized tools.It's worth noting that to fully utilize the capabilities of this RAM kit, your laptop's motherboard and chipset must support DDR5 memory technology. Compatibility should be verified before purchasing to ensure seamless integration and optimal performance.In conclusion, the Crucial RAM 64GB Kit (2x32GB) DDR5 4800MHz CL40 Laptop Memory is a top-tier memory solution that brings enhanced performance and ample capacity to your laptop. With its impressive speed, substantial capacity, and reliable performance, this RAM kit is ideal for power users, content creators, and gamers who require high memory bandwidth and multitasking capabilities. Upgrade your laptop with this cutting-edge memory solution and experience a significant boost in performance and responsiveness for your demanding tasks.", "Wanted to run more things on the laptop and it was struggling with just the occasional multitasking due to RAM resources with 2x8 ( 16 GB ) of RAM.Followed a review stating it has worked for an Alienware M17 but not a specific R# Setup.I didn't want to rip my entire laptop apart just to unplug my CMOS battery to reset the BIOS. So all I did was disconnect the battery, removed the old RAM, put in the new RAM and let it run until the CMOS essentially had reset itself after 10-ish attempts to boot up.You are prompted to reset your values in your BIOS and you should choose to do so, so that you can boot up the laptop afterwards.All is working and running really well.I can multitask a lot of RAM dependent applications and I also can run a heavily modified Minecraft Server that takes around 16-24 GB's of RAM with around 200+ mods to boot along with having 10 players in the server.I really recommend this RAM set for those wanting to go from 16 > 64 or even 32 > 64 GBs.It works flawless with no errors or BSODS of any kind.Take this chance at this price point!", 'Purchased this memory to upgrade my 2023 Dell XPS15 from 16GB to 64GB of memory.The back of the laptop came apart easily and installation was a breeze.The laptop does take a while to boot 1st time and does throw up a screen that indicated memory size has changed, but it\'s simply "OK" and it boots up.Since first boot in now boots normally and works flawlessly.If you\'re after a memory upgrade for your XPS 15 I\'d recommend these Crucial DDR5 modules.', 'F√ºr ein Laptop Upgrade perfekt ! Der Ram wurde bei mir ( Asus A15 2023 ) direkt erkannt und l√§uft Stabil.F√ºr Mini PCs oder sonstiges bedenken der Ram hier l√§uft wirklich nur auf Werkstakt welcher von OEM Board ben√∂tigt wird. F√ºr den Einsatz im PC oder Laptop mit Unlocked BIOS zum einstellen der XMP w√ºrde ich h√∂here MHZ und niedrigere CL timings nehmen 5600 CL 36 z.b. da bekommt man wieder gut Performance f√ºr relativ wenig Geld.Jedoch wie im Falle des Asus mit Locked Bios und eingestellten Ram Geschwindigkeiten Top Ram f√ºr allem f√ºr den Preis ( Gekauft f√ºr 32‚Ç¨ / 16GB Riegel )', "Bought this for my 2023 M15 R7 (i7 3070ti.  16 GB Ram), since when I was running Diablo 4 my memory would be almost about 90%. I wanted to double it since the game would lag if I switched back and forth between the game and chrome. I am also one that leaves a bunch of tabs open on my browser.Steps:1) SHUT DOWN computer2) Remove the screws from the bottom (two wouldn't come out all the way because of the washers)3) Run the case, I used a guitar pick like tool to help pop things up the end of case4) Optional: remove the battery connection (I did not do this)5) Push the two tabs from the Ram stick so it'll pop up and replace them (x2). Make sure everything lines up push it in firmly and then push down so the tabs will click that means it's good to go.6) close up the bottom cover and push down along the edges so it clicks7) put that the screws in8) press the power button (rainbow keyboards showing should be good, it takes about 5-10 minutes to load)8) screen should detect new memory capacity just click okay/apply9) it should restart again and windows should load up and you're good to go!Works perfectly!", 'Ainda √© muito cedo pra que eu possa confirmar a qualidade do produto, mas de antem√£o posso dizer que a instala√ß√£o foi simples e r√°pida.', 'Dell G15 ÔΩπÔæûÔΩ∞ÔæêÔæùÔΩ∏Ôæû Laptop „ÅÆ„É°„É¢„É™Â¢óË®≠Áî®„Å´Ë≥ºÂÖ•„ÄÇ‰ª•ÂâçÂà•„ÅÆ„ÇÇ„ÅÆÔºà16GB√ó2ÊûöÔºâ„ÇíË≥ºÂÖ•„Åó„Åü„Å®„Åç„Å´„ÅØÁõ∏ÊÄßÂïèÈ°å„ÅßÂãï‰Ωú„Åó„Åæ„Åõ„Çì„Åß„Åó„Åü„Åå„ÄÅ„Åì„Å°„Çâ„ÅÆ„É°„É¢„É™Ôºà16GB√ó2ÊûöÔºâ„ÅØÂãï‰Ωú„Åó„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇDDRÔºî„É°„É¢„É™„Åß„ÅØÁõ∏ÊÄßÂïèÈ°å„ÅÆË©±„ÇíËÅû„Åã„Å™„Åè„Å™„Çä„Åæ„Åó„Åü„Åå„ÄÅ„Åæ„Å†Êñ∞„Åó„ÅÑDDR5„É°„É¢„É™„Å´„ÅØÁõ∏ÊÄßÂïèÈ°å„ÅåÊúâ„Çã„Çà„ÅÜ„Åß„Åô„ÄÇ„Å™„ÅäÂãï‰Ωú„ÅÆÂÆâÂÆöÊÄß„Å´„Å§„ÅÑ„Å¶„ÅØ„ÄÅ„É°„É¢„É™„ÇíÊèõË£Ö„Åó„Å¶„Åó„Å∞„Çâ„Åè„ÅØ‰∏çÂÆâÂÆö„Å™„Åì„Å®„ÇÇ„ÅÇ„Çä„Åæ„Åó„Åü„Åå„ÄÅ„ÅÑ„Å§„ÅÆÈñì„Å´„ÅãÂÆâÂÆö„Åó„Å¶Âãï‰Ωú„Åô„Çã„Çà„ÅÜ„Å´„Å™„Çä„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇ„ÇÇ„Åó„Åã„Åô„Çã„Å®Widows„Ç¢„ÉÉ„Éó„Éá„Éº„Éà„ÅÆÂΩ±Èüø„ÇÇ„ÅÇ„Çã„ÅÆ„Åã„ÇÇ„Åó„Çå„Åæ„Åõ„Çì„ÄÇ']

Reviews: ['Was working beautiful for 3 years...and recently started getting bsod regularly. didnt expect a reliable brand like crucial to be the cause but had to yank it out and get my sanity back ah well.', 'Received in good condition. Shipping to SG is fast', 'This works with Asustor NAS', "took me a while to upgrade my mac mini early 2020 version, but that's because of the compactness of everything in the mini's motherboard and the ancientness of my eyes, lol! actually i had to redo everything because of the way the ram modules are clasped and held together in the mini, but 3rd time lucky, the mac started up and showed that it indeed had 32gb as memory... after that, i never had any problems with my mini.... thank you!", 'Faster than the stock ram that came with my laptop', 'Easy to install, and is blazing fast.No problem encountered after installing.The trick, though, is to know how to remove the old RAMs.There is a small clip at the side. So I take out the original ones, use only the new 32GB kit at the slots that original ram placed and it works! After awhile, I insert back the original ram in another 2 slots and it finally work out!!! So far got no problem, and I happy with result.', "The memory modules work great. The tricky part is getting the Mac Mini opened up and disassembled to get at the memory slots. The trick is to have the torx screw preinserted into the hole and held in place (before you try to align it i to the screw hole and turning the screw into the hole) so it won't get pulled under the nearby magnet and requiring dismounting of the mainboard to retrieve the screw.", 'Arrived on time as it should as stated by Amazon.I have previously been using Crucial for my iMac since 2 years back with the first being 32GB Ram of 2x16GB. This is an add on and it seems to be working well when I plugged in.', 'good quality, works well, competitively priced']

Super raro (ahora que lo pienso deb√≠ revisar el numero de serie, pero no lo hice, oh vaya).Para abrir la iMac es un show, pero con los tutoriales que hay en everymac se hace r√°pido. Vieles geht nun besser und schneller, von dem ich nicht einmal geahnt habe, das mehr Speicher helfen k√∂nnte‚Ä¶Wirklich lohnenswert!', 'Avevo acquistato il prodotto precedentemente e purtroppo dopo 20 giorni i banchi di memoria non funzionavano pi√π ho rifatto l‚Äôacquisto pi√π di sei mesi fa sempre per le RAM da 16 G e devo dire che funzionano perfettamente non hanno dato pi√π problemi e sono compatibili al 100% con il mio iMac 21,5‚Äú', 'to me most important in my quest was to find a reliable and working Memory upgrade that would be accepted and working in my DS920+ Synology NAS  - The CT16G4S266M does answer these requirements.', "I didn't have any problem with the memory itself. The only issue I had was in actually installing the memory. I had attempted to upgrade the memory when I first bought this 27in iMac (mid-2019 model) and failed, even though I had with tech support. They couldn't figure out why and I just returned it. This was from another memory company that has a pretty good reputation. A friend of mine recommended Crucial brand memory and I found the right memory here on Amazon. After I ordered the memory I checked on the internet and found a computer geek with the same set up, even with the memory upgrade - 8Gb OEM, adding 16Gb. He stated make the memory arrangement thus - Bank 1 = 4 Gb + 8GB; Bank 2 = 4 Gb + 8GB. Booted up the first time. No issues so far. Mahalo."]

Product: Crucial RAM 32GB Kit (16GBx2) DDR4 3200MHz CL22 (or 2933MHz or 2666MHz) Desktop Memory CT2K16G4DFD832A
Reviews: ['', "Computer Memory - they just work until they don't", '„Åì„ÅÆÈáëÈ°ç„Åß„Åì„ÅÆÂÜÖÂÆπ„Å™„ÇâÊñáÂè•„Å™„Åè„Ç≥„Çπ„ÉëÊúÄÈ´ò„Åß„Åô„ÄÇ', 'Worked perfectly for my Hewlett Packard desktop gaming model tg01-0023w. (Entry level gaming desktop for 599.00) You cant beat that with these crazy current gpu prices in which most are marked up from anywhere to twice and up 3-4 times their value (April 2021) because of greedy scalpers and covid-19, which is over hyped hysteria imo. Watched some YouTube videos and I wanted to learn how to upgrade the computers ram and went from the factory 8gb to 32gb which is this particular model motherboards  max ram, and did it with ease, literally just plug and play (Ive never done this before) and didn‚Äôt have to worry about messing with ryzen master or trying to adjust ram speeds in the bios.  My pc instantly recognized this awesome crucial ram and runs it at 3200 mhz as advertised. Definitely made a difference in my computers performance! Would recommend this ram and this computer, Ive never had a gaming pc until now, and always wanted to make that transition from console to pc. Fortnite looks awesome and runs great now.  Getting 240 fps @1080p on my first ever gaming pc, paired with a LG 240hz monitor which is too sweet! Definitely getting the most performance out this little pc with a simple ram upgrade!  I am extremely satisfied now, although the monitor was not cheap but worth it imo, I should be good to go for a long time.', "Pros: It works with the Lenovo Legion Tower 7i Desktop, it's very easy to install, after having it for over a month I haven't had any issues with it casuing crashes, lagging etc. My PC runs a bit smoother overall, and exports videos faster, with this RAM (had 16GB previously now have 32GB RAM after this upgrade). Has plug and play functionality with the adverised 3200mhz spees running right after install no need to change things in the BIOS. And it comes with a lifetime warranty.Cons: Unattractive basic design, It's expensive in my opinion. I got this for around $145 but the current price is now over $200 CAD! In just a month the price increased rapidly which I definitely don't like and would recommend others try to snag this on sale, or consider buying from Amazon US which has this priced much lower (even with conversion) than it is in Canada right now as of posting this review in August 2022.Overall I would recommend this Crucial DDR4 RAM to others üëçüèæ", "Comprate per l'upgrade massimo della RAM al mio Computer... che dire... da 16 GB installati (appena acquistato) al massimo 64 GB DDR4... √® velocissimo, e molto pi√π fluido e veloce in tutto!Consiglio sempre di andare sul sito ufficiale e di controllare il modello del vostro Computer, inserendo la marca, il modello, oppure con il software che controlla le parti giuste da acquistare per l'upgrade!Ottime in tutto consigliate!!! ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è", "The Crucial website said this RAM was compatible with a Lenovo Legion T7-34IMZ5.  Sadly, the RAM I received was either incompatible or damaged.  I tried multiple install solutions but every time got the motherboard beeps of incompatibility and/or bad memory.  Not questioning the value of the RAM just that it didn't work for me on a Legion T7-34IMZ5...and this model is a real pain to get memory.", "Plugged right in, works fine.  This RAM is clocked slower than a lot of the DDR4 RAM on the market, but in my experience usually going with faster clocks isn't worth it.  You might gain maybe 1% going with faster RAM, but you would have to test very carefully to detect it.I put 4 of these 32 GB modules into my new Ryzen3 5800X build, and I am completely satisfied.", "Whilst not officially supported in the HP MicroServer Gen10 Plus this kit works fine and I now have 64GB installed (which is the maximum the CPU and chipset support).I've had no issues at all and this has made the HP MicroServer Gen10 Plus into a decent little VMware ESXi host.I really wanted an ECC kit for the server but they seem to be impossible to find at the moment. I'm not really running any important production stuff and it's more for a home lab so I'm happy to use this non-ECC kit instead.", "They are what they are , so far so good no problems. Just really simple , no RGB, no Fancy smancy case around 'em, but I knew this when I ordered. Pro is they are running great in my system. CON for the money you'd think they might be alil fancier with some RGB or at least a color case. But hey is it about looks or performance? Maybe I'll just grab the accessory RGB cases for any DDR. Which makes 32GB into well over 200 for mid grade thats pricey..."]

Product: Crucial RAM 32GB DDR5 5200MHz (or 4800MHz) Laptop Memory CT32G52C42S5
Reviews: ["Works fine for weeks now. I bought 2 so I'm running 64GB on my laptop. I'm always decompressing large files so this reduced the stress on my nvme since I have only set my pagefile to 1GB", 'Der RAM war einer der g√ºnstigsten DDR5 RAMs zum Kauf und funktionierte auf Anhieb als Erweiterung in meinem HP Elitebook. Ansonsten macht er auch keine Probleme, was will man mehr. Insgesamt bin ich sehr zufrieden mit meinem Kauf und die Statistik des Crucial-RAMs in meinen anderen Systemen l√§sst auch hier auf lange Lebensdauer hoffen.', 'Im Gegensatz zu den "Mondpreisen", die DELL f√ºr RAM verlangt, ist der Crucial SO-DIMM DDR5 gerade zu ein Schn√§ppchen.Nach dem Einbau und ersten Hochfahren braucht das System ein paar Minuten (Tastaturbeleuchtung ein, aber noch nicht am Bildschirm zu sehen), danach kommt die Meldung vom BIOS "Amount of Memoy has been changed". Dann best√§tigen, alles ok. Zur Sicherheit habe ich das DELL Diagnoseprogramm noch zweimal laufen lassen, m einwandfreie Funktion zu testen, ein echter Gewinn mit jetzt 2 x 32 GB DDR5 RAM, wenn man z.B. sehr gro√üe Bilder bearbeitet oder mit virtuellen Maschinen arbeitet.', 'The first stick of 32 GB DDR5 I got was finnicky. This is the first stick of RAM I\'ve ever had in around 20 years that gave a "RAM Defective" error code.No problem, Crucial replaced it.The second stick worked. But memory training (black screen pre-POST) took somewhere around 5 minutes. A frightening amount of time since that long of a black screen usually means something is wrong.BE PAITENT. Let your computer sit on the black screen for at least 10 minutes to be safe. It will boot normally on future boots.', "Apr√®s remplacement des barrettes m√©moire d'origine (2x8Go) par celles ci (2x16Go), tout fonctionne tr√®s bien , pas de diff√©rence notable de rapidit√© de chargement , par contre si beaucoup de logiciels ouvert ainsi que de nombreux onglets ouvert sur chrome , le pc reste fluide est pas de lag.Je suis satisfait de ces barrettes m√©moire qui on permit d'augmenter les capacit√©s de mon Pc.", 'Really just leaving a review for informational purposes.Bought a Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Extreme Gen 5 with just 8GB of RAM preinstalled... which of course is criminal. Got this Crucial 32GB to beef it up quite a bit... installed it, and got a quizzical LED code of FnLock/Esc + F1 + F4, blinking in sequential order. Of course, I did my troubleshooting... and of course, I had installed an m.2 SSD as well, which didn\'t help in simplifying what was wrong.However, long story short, that FnLock/Esc + F1 + F4 LED blinking in sequential order is literally just it loading. Let it sit and "load" and recognize the RAM... and it should be fine! (I now have 40GB of RAM in this thing.)', 'Funktioniert bislang tadellos mit meinem Inspirion 16 plus 7620.Was man aber wirklich beachten muss. Nach dem Einbau bzw. Tausch des Modules tut sich beim Einschalten des Notebooks f√ºr ca. 2 - 3 Minuten gar nicht. Die Tastaturbeleuchtung geht an, mehr passiert nicht, auch kein Bios Alarm gepiepe. Man muss hier wirklich einfach Geduld haben. Es folgt dann ein Hinweis aus dem Bios auf dem Bildschirm, dass die Hardware ge√§ndert wurde. Diese kann man dann quittieren, dann gibt es keine Probleme mehr.', "Got a new laptop and once I saw that the fresh copy of windows was already hogging 7 out of 16gb or RAM, I started looking into upgrades.  Have read mixed reviews on what is and isn't compatible with my laptop (Dell G16 - #7620).  Used Crucials website and this was one of the options. Product: Crucial Ballistix 3200 MHz DDR4 DRAM Laptop Gaming Memory Kit 32GB (16GBx2) CL16 BL2K16G32C16S4B
Reviews: ["Comparing to my other RAM modules, the built quality is very good. I'm using 2 x 8GB 3200 Mhz modules in my ASRock X300 Ryzen 5 4650G Pro system and overclocked it to 3400. Works flawlessly ;)", 'Works fine with my ROG Strix scar III. No issues or whatsoever.', 'Fast ram, used in an intel NUC with an RTX 2060 works great', '', 'Pop it in, turn on XMP and it works perfectly as described. Great product!', 'good purchase but you must ensure your bios is xmp enabled', 'Antes que nada, decir que estoy devolviendo estas memorias. He quedad completamente decepcionado del p√©simo funcionamiento que tienen. Es m√°s, he quedado negativamente sorprendido. Esencialmente, ha sido invertir 350‚Ç¨ para que mi ordenador ande, en el mejor de los casos, igual que antes‚Äîpero incluso m√°s lento en ciertas circunstancias! Uno puede decir que tal vez la diferencia sea mayor o menor dado un factor u otro (en efecto, Crucial, al contactarme con ellos, culp√≥ al BIOS, a los drivers, a mi disco r√≠gido, etc.) pero si he subido de 16Gb de RAM a 64Gb de RAM, lo m√≠nimo es encontrarse con que el ordenador sea UN POCO m√°s veloz‚Ä¶ Encontrarse que no est√° igual que antes, o incluso peor, es inexplicable.Primero mencionar√© a cualquier interesado que estas memorias no son plug-n-play, sino que requieren de XMP para funcionar a la velocidad que dicen. De modo que si tu ordenador no tiene XMP activado, no permite activarlo y/o no permite configurar el overclocking, ni pienses en comprarlas, pues estar√°s pagando por 3200MHz y recibiendo solo 2666MHz. Es decir que estar√°s probablemente desperdiciando dinero.Ya me parec√≠a raro que estuvieran m√°s baratas que la mayor√≠a. Pero eso lo explica. Para comenzar, funcionan con XMP, con que cuestan menos que las que andan directamente. Y luego el hecho de que no me han funcionado bien, con lo que oigo la voz de mi abuelo: lo barato sale caro!Y es que el punto, la raz√≥n por la que las compr√©, fue que para ser un kit de 64Gb @ 3200MHz est√° al menos 100 m√°s barato que otros. Pero no le√≠ en ninguna parte que fuera XMP. Las compr√© para la HP OMEN 15-en0003ns y lamentablemente, a estas alturas, y a pesar de ser un ordenador para gaming, a√∫n no tiene soporte de XMP u overclocking. En fin, solo ha sido luego de investigar en l√≠nea que me di cuenta que para conseguir los 3200MHz de este RAM tendr√≠a que tener acceso a algo que mi ordenador no tiene acceso. Pero debo mencionar que esta es la memoria que me fue recomendada para mi modelo espec√≠fico de ordenador en la misma p√°gina de Crucial. Luego el soporte de Crucial me confirma que esta memoria requiere de XMP y que mi ordenador no lo tiene; de modo que recomiendan ellos mismos una memoria que saben que no va andar correctamente.El RAM original de mi Omen es de 16Gb (2x8GB) y anda correctamente a 3200MHz porque es de Samsung y, entonces, plug-n-play. Es m√°s, al realizar una prueba de benchmark me sale como ‚Äú103% Outstanding‚Äù, que quiere decir Sobresaliente; y ‚ÄúPerforming way above expectations (94th percentile)‚Äù que quiere decir que anda mucho mejor de lo que se espera de esa memoria y que est√° en el percentil 94. Con lo que solo 6% de memorias similares funcionan mejor que la m√≠a. En general, con la memoria original instalada el benchmark me dice que mi Omen est√° en el percentil 48% para gaming, el 95% como ordenador de escritorio y el 48% como m√°quina de trabajo; y que ‚ÄúEn general, esta PC est√° funcionando por encima de las expectativas (percentil 75). Esto significa que de 100 PC con exactamente los mismos componentes, 25 funcionaron mejor.‚ÄùSin embargo, le pongo estas RAM de 64Gb y directamente baja a 2667Mhz, me dice que es ‚Äúdesconocido‚Äù y que son 2x31.5GB (y no 2x32Gb). Me dice que su performance est√° en ‚Äú69.8% Good‚Äù, es decir Buena‚Ä¶ y ‚ÄúPerforming way below expectations (4th percentile)‚Äù, que quiere decir que anda MUY POR DEBAJO de las expectativas, y que est√° en el 4to percentil‚Ä¶ es decir que el 96% de memorias andan mejor! Y en general ahora coloca mi Omen a 41% para gaming, 87% como ordenador de escritorio y 41% como ordenador de trabajo. Y me dice: ‚ÄúEn general, esta PC se est√° desempe√±ando por debajo de las expectativas (percentil 39). Esto significa que de 100 PC con exactamente los mismos componentes, 61 funcionaron mejor. El percentil general de PC es el promedio de cada uno de sus componentes individuales. Utilice los gr√°ficos de las secciones de referencia de este informe para identificar las √°reas problem√°ticas.‚Äù (Y el √°rea problem√°tica es la memoria, obviamente, pues todo el resto funciona como antes.)De modo que ya ves que 350‚Ç¨ me ha costado retroceder mi ordenador a un estado peor del que estaba inicialmente! Obviamente que no me iba a quedar con las memorias‚Ä¶Pero igual decid√≠ hacer otras pruebas y, adem√°s, ver si es que hab√≠a alguna manera de ponerlas a la altura que deber√≠an estar.En t√©rminos de mis pruebas con lo que trabajo a diario, que es la edici√≥n de v√≠deo y post-producci√≥n, los resultados en t√©rminos de render y exportaci√≥n fueron iguales que antes. No me esperaba que fuera un cambio muy dram√°tico, pues estas cosas m√°s tienen que ver con CPU y GPU, pero s√≠ que me esperaba alg√∫n cambio, as√≠ sea ligero, para mejor. En el mejor de los casos, los tiempos se mantuvieron iguales; pero cuando cambiaron, fue para INCREMENTAR y no reducir. As√≠ fue que not√© que en exportaci√≥n de 3D est√° un 3% m√°s lenta y que en exportaci√≥n de Premiere Pro est√° entre 9-10% m√°s lenta. En After Effects y dem√°s, el tiempo se mantuvo igual.Ya es suficiente para que yo sepa que no vale la pena la inversi√≥n de 350‚Ç¨, pues yo necesito al menos alguna mejora en t√©rminos de velocidad en estas aplicaciones. No obstante, ni siquiera en aspectos que no dependen del GPU/CPU mejor√≥ en velocidad: las aplicaciones demoran igual en abrir y estar listas para usar (incluso not√© que el After Effects demoraba m√°s), el uso de las mismas no es m√°s r√°pido (incluso el Playback se mantuvo pr√°cticamente como antes), etc.Y en t√©rminos subjetivos, es decir, en lo que pude percibir al usar el ordenador, navegar por √©l, abrir otras aplicaciones como Word o Chrome, al abrir carpetas, etc., no not√© ninguna diferencia! Si not√© algo, he sentido que fue para mal‚Ä¶ espec√≠ficamente cuando se trata de acceder a mi disco externo de 8Tb WD MyBook: not√© que demoraba m√°s en cargar proyectos que estaban archivados ah√≠. Adem√°s, he sentido que el Windows 10 me carga a la misma velocidad.Entonces me comuniqu√© con Crucial directamente y les coment√© todo lo que aqu√≠ les comento a ustedes‚Ä¶ Su respuesta no tom√≥ en cuenta los tests de benchmark o mis pruebas con los programas de edici√≥n que uso, sino se enfoc√≥ en que el Windows no carga m√°s r√°pido y culp√≥ al BIOS, al Windows y a mis drivers, que hab√≠a que mantener todos actualizados; culp√≥ al hardware de mi ordenador, que hab√≠a que hacer tests de que no estuviera da√±ado; y culp√≥ a mi disco r√≠gido‚Ä¶ Les expliqu√© que hace una semana realic√© tests completos (que los hago cada cierto tiempo) y que todo estaba andando al 100%; que todo estaba completamente actualizado, incluyendo el BIOS; y que nada hab√≠a cambiado en mi ordenador, excepto las memorias RAM! Y que antes de colocarlas todo andaba perfectamente, de modo que c√≥mo pod√≠a ser culpa de otra cosa que no fuera la √∫nica variable: las memorias! Siguieron empecinados en lo mismo y, pues, como yo no quiero perder mi tiempo, con eso me decid√≠ a devolver las memorias inmediatamente y regresar a como estaba antes‚Ä¶ y esperar a ahorrar un poco m√°s para invertir en unas RAM de una marca que s√≠ conozca.Ahora, incluso si se dieran los problemas que alega Crucial, no hay manera que con 4 veces la velocidad RAM no haya siquiera una m√≠nima mejor√≠a‚Ä¶ Eso me parece imposible.Ahora que estoy de vuelta con mi m√≠sero RAM de 16Gb vuelvo a tener los resultados sobresalientes que mencion√© al principio, mi ordenador anda igual y, en el mejor de los casos, me parece que en general anda mejor que con las de Crucial.Ser√≠a f√°cil adjudicar los problemas al hecho de e que en vez de andar a 3200MHz las Crucial andan a 2667MHz en mi ordenador, pero la verdad que la diferencia en esa velocidad deber√≠a ser m√≠nima en la mayor√≠a de usos, sobre todo en los que a m√≠ me interesan. Y luego est√° el hecho de que incluso andando m√°s lento en esos t√©rminos, el hecho de que hablamos de 48Gb m√°s, es decir de 4 veces la capacidad RAM, como digo arriba en el peor de los casos absolutamente tendr√≠a que haber al menos una m√≠nima mejor√≠a en velocidad‚Ä¶ y no la hubo.', 'Las uso para un port√°til gaming y hasta ahora no he tenido ning√∫n problema con ellas, funcionan genial y en resumidas es lo que indica el propio producto', "So I want to begin with the Intel XMP preset settings. It does appear that it's more likely required to select the profile in the bios with a good cold restart before you actually see the results. Other than that test. This is the ultimate generic product. The hard posted sticker on the product picture and description is nothing more than just a plastic sticker. This is not exactly a problem. I already reconsidered the amount of cooling and just plain cool accessories for the mobile platform the list goes all the way down to none and never will be required. There is no room for extra plates. This ram is of course goes great with the Intel NUC6i7KYK kit. And it is pretty much doing everything as expected with just the basic destinations as a personal media computer that does other network jobs. The list is very simple network storage, remote host and virtual machine host. And it actually can do more than expected as a single working computer. What I can show right now is only just the basic benchmark performance that's used 24/7. And with the kit package I only get better performance. The speed is great at 3200mhz and never really changes. It comepletly changed the freezing problems for the kit aswell, in my opinion. I never really had problems filling up the most possible ram in the computer with any technical issues. The computer always accepted more than indicated by the CPU specifications. And I would go with the maximum of 64gb. I just considered the value and the every day use for the 32gb kit. I have seen a performance boost and quality in contrast to store product quality, but I unfortunatelly do not have any benchmark copies left. All I can say is that the limit reached is pretty much the same as raced. It recieved a very high score as is without any unrequired CPU clock changes. As always I don't like the undesired settings to bolster the loose ends, it's just a package that works after the finally good research for this weird compatibility blame.", 'Upgraded a new Asus TUF506IV from stock 8GB 3200MHz CL22.  The Crucial 64GB memory installed easily, system PassMark rating was 4575 (compared to original 4490), and MemTest86 ran 8-10 hours with no errors.  Sounds good, but on my non-XMP system it runs at its (non-advertised) JEDEC speed of 2666MHz CL20.  So it is indeed solid, reliable memory from a trusted vendor, and increased my system\'s memory by 4x at no speed loss.However, another vendor\'s product advertised JEDEC (not XMP) speeds of 3200MHz CL18 for a similar price.  First shipment failed MemTest86 in the first hour.  Replacement passed MemTest86 11+ hours and is now running at advertised speed, which lowers latency from stock CL22 to CL18.  PassMark now scores 4793 (vs 4575).My greatest disappointment is that a brand I trusted, Crucial, was not upfront about the need for XMP to achieve advertised speed.  Maybe it\'s my own stupidity, but not everyone knows about that subtle difference between interchangeable XMP 1.35V and JEDEC 1.2V products.  Their product support folks defend their website assertion that "it\'s compatible" with my system, by noting that it does indeed run and is reliable, just slower.I don\'t know if a 300-point PassMark difference matters (not much), or if the speed difference matters, I\'m just put out that I only became aware of the issue (due to my ignorance about XMP/JEDEC speed variances) after my purchase, and it complicated a simple upgrade with some hours of additional research and support calls while the product was already on the way.Score:  When first Crucial shipment arrived, bag was empty (improperly sealed); Amazon replaced no problem, second set worked well, though slower than expected.  First "other brand" shipment failed testing; Amazon replaced no problem, second set worked well and at expected speeds, and it\'s running  in my system now.Help us understand, Crucial.  You\'ve been trusted for years.  Saying up front that "in non-XMP systems the memory will revert to JEDEC speeds", or even saying "XMP>3200, JEDEC>2666" somewhere would\'ve helped.']

Avec une garantie qui accompagne cette m√©moire, vous pouvez avoir l'esprit tranquille quant √† votre investissement.En conclusion, la m√©moire Corsair Vengeance DDR5 64 Go est une v√©ritable prouesse technologique qui √©l√®ve votre exp√©rience informatique √† des sommets in√©gal√©s. Ses performances √©blouissantes, son design √©l√©gant et sa fiabilit√© √† toute √©preuve en font un choix indiscutable pour les utilisateurs √† la recherche de l'ultime √©volution de la m√©moire informatique. Corsair a une fois de plus prouv√© pourquoi il est un leader de confiance dans l'industrie, et la Vengeance DDR5 en est la preuve vivante.", 'o pre√ßo √© alto,mas vale cada centavo.produto excelente.', 'Ottima', "Memory works great with XMP enabled on the botherboard, I was able to get the advertised clock speeds with default XMP profile settings.  Nice!Installed pretty easily, though the heat spreaders aren't flush against the top of the dimm.This means if you push on the heat spreaders to seat the sticks, you can bust up the thermal connection a bit.  Press on the corners to install and it's not a problem.Solid RAM at a good price for the latency!", 'I use this in a water cooled Dell XPS 8960 workstation. I also placed a  fan cooled heat sink on the SSD that vents across this SDRAM. It all has stayed cool. Even when rendering complex scenes, it remains cool.', 'Recomiendo esta memoria a 5200Hz, perfecta para placa Asus Z790 Maximus Hero si quieres usar el maximo de memoria que admite el procesador 13900K.Si vas a usar menos memoria RAM hay opciones de mayor velocidad disponible, es importante ver la pagina de compatibilidad de Asus.Recomiendo configurar el XMP II y hacer un test de memoria desde la BIOS de Asus y desde Windows.Comparto estos detalles porque me costo llegar hasta esta configuraci√≥n optima y para que os sea util.', '64GB RAM (2x32GB), Corsair Vengeance DDR5, CMK64GX5M2B5200C40.I had initially bought a Crucial 64GB RAM kit from Amazon (2x32GB DDR5_4800MHz CL40 Desktop Memory CT2K32G48C40U5) which *did not boot up at all* on my Dell desktop/XPS-8950 i7-12700K after many configuration tries.  I was "sold" on the Crucial kit by all the positive XPS-8950 reviews.I contacted Crucial and they stated some RAM needs to be "trained" on a system, tweak the BIOS, etc.  I just returned the Crucial kit and picked up the Corsair kit for about the same money.  I\'m glad I did.The Corsair Vengeance kit booted on the first try.  It actually installed more easily too as the build quality is better than run-of-the-mill RAM (including the Crucial kit).  Unfortunately, Dell is charging around $313 for 32GB (not 64GB) of RAM these days (as of July, 2023).  Corsair was the way to go for me for price, compatibility and quality.']

Reviews: ['', 'Have not yet tried. Although the box came in dented, but still worth the buy!', 'Very nice colour! Loving the white exterior', "1. I'm seeing some confusion here. Go to your motherboard manufacturer's website, go to your motherboard model page, click something like 'download' / 'support' / 'bios' (w/e the site happen to label it as). There ought to be one which includes 'AGESA' in the title. There should also be some instructions there on how to update your BIOS. Update it, go into your BIOS, set the memory OC profile. Chances are your BIOS will have a predefined one you can just click on, it might even be called 'XMP', which will work fine.If, for any reason, your BIOS doesn't have a fitting predefined memory profile, just manually enter the speed & timing (this kit ,CMT32GX5M2X6200C36, is 6200mhz 36-39-39-76), save & exit, enjoy functionality.2. Product: Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro SL 32GB (2x16GB) DDR4 3600 (PC4-28800) C18 1.35V Optimized for AMD Ryzen - Black (CMH32GX4M2Z3600C18)
Reviews: ['Corsair, reliable as always.  Great RAM brand and love the RGB lighting!', 'Avevo necessit√† di upgradare il mio computer da 16 a 32Gb di RAM, e di questi tempi, per le DDR4, non c\'√® pi√π tanta differenza in fatto di prezzo nelle combinazioni di velocit√† e latenze pi√π comuni, e i banchi con RGB spesso si trovano a meno di 10 euro in pi√π rispetto ai banchi "lisci", almeno per quanto riguarda queste ram da gaming col dissipatore figo. Prima avevo le Kingston Fury bianche che vedete nella foto, 16Gb, con timings 3200 CL16. Queste sono la versione "SL" delle Vengeance RGB, leggermente pi√π basse delle RGB non "SL", che arrivano a circa 5CM di altezza contro i 4.5Cm di queste (che comunque sono parecchio alte e infatti sul mio PC toccano i tubi dell\'AIO), ma per il resto sono pressoch√© identiche. Nella foto vedete la differenza tra questa, le Kingston Fury, e un banco di ram OEM.In ogni caso, oramai le uniche combinazioni di latenza e velocit√† che vale la pena comprare sono o queste da 3600 CL18, o le 3200 CL16. Non sto a scrivere una tesi ingegneristica su come funzionano le latenze delle RAM, sappiate solo che tra queste due combinazioni di velocit√† e latenza, la latenza effettiva della memoria √® sostanzialmente la stessa (infatti non noto nessuna differenza, ma proprio zero, tra le Kingston 3200CL16 e queste 3600CL18).Generalmente le 3600CL18 costano un po\' di pi√π perch√© hanno un po\' pi√π margine di overclock (o possono essere portate a clock pi√π bassi con latenza pi√π bassa come per esempio 3200 CL14, migliorando la latenza assoluta). Per me non ne vale la pena, preferisco giocare ai videogiochi piuttosto che passare i giorni a settare timings e voltaggi a mano per un miglioramento nei benchmark statici dell\'1%, magari per poi trovarmi con il sistema instabile all\'improvviso dopo un mese di apparente stabilit√†.Nel mio caso poi, che ho un processore 5800X3D, la cache L3 di 96Mb del processore rende pressoch√© nullo qualsiasi guadagno si possa ottenere da RAM pi√π veloci, in quanto specialmente nel gaming tutto ci√≤ che serve al processore √® caricato nella cache L3, le letture dirette dalla RAM diventano quindi meno frequenti. In altre parole, la velocit√† delle RAM passa totalmente in secondo piano.Oltre a questo, generalmente su tutti i banchi di RAM la base (JEDEC) √® la stessa, ovvero 2133 CL15. Poi dal bios si imposta il profilo XMP o DOCP, che √® salvato in modo permanente nel banco di RAM dal produttore e contiene tutti i timings, voltaggi e quant\'altro per farle andare alla velocit√† che avete pagato e che √® scritta sulla scatola. La differenza fisica quindi tra una 3200 CL16 e una 4000 CL20 √® inesistente perch√© il JEDEC √® lo stesso, prendendo RAM pi√π veloci andrete a pagare il fatto che il produttore ha testato il banco con velocit√† pi√π spinte e l\'ha certificato inserendolo nel profilo XMP. E tutto questo per cosa? Magari andrete a pagare il 50% in pi√π di prezzo per un incremento prestazionale STATICO del 1-5% nel migliore dei casi (e dello 0.x% nel gaming specialmente se avete un processore come il mio). Direi quindi che se la matematica non mi inganna, pagare il 50% in pi√π per un incremento prestazionale dell\'1-5% non vale la pena!Quindi perch√© ho preso le 3600CL18?Perch√© le ho prese usate con Amazon Seconda Mano e costavano meno delle 3200CL16. Ed √® quello che consiglio a chiunque, prendete quelle che costano meno, se non fate overclock estremo per il gusto di farlo, ve ne potete altamente fregare di queste faccende, e vi prego, state lontani da qualsiasi banco di ram che non sia una delle due combinazioni citate sopra, ovvero 3600 CL18 e 3200 CL16, andreste a pagare magari il 50% in pi√π per un incremento nelle prestazioni STATICHE di 1-5% se va bene e letteralmente zero nel gaming.Bene, abbiamo appurato che dei timing e della velocit√† ce ne possiamo altamente fregare, quindi parliamo di cose SERIE, di quello che interessa davvero a noi GAMERS, ovvero di lucine colorate.Ognuna di queste ha ben 10 leddini RGB personalizzabili. Se come nel mio caso avete tutto della NZXT, e che quindi state gi√† usando l\'odiatissimo NZXT-CAM per controllare i vari leddini che avete in giro sparsi nel case, per controllare queste dovrete installare Corsair iCUE, che √® uno dei peggiori abomini software che io abbia mai visto. √à talmente un abominio che in confronto ad iCUE quella mostruosit√† che √® l\'Asus Armoury Crate sembra quasi accettabile.Vi dico solo che iCue √® un download da 1.5Gb, che una volta installato occupa 3.5Gb su disco. E io mi chiedo, ma veramente servono 3.5Gb di dati non meglio identificati per controllare 10 leddini su delle RAM? Bloatware allo stato puro.In ogni caso, per quanto mi faccia schifo iCue, c\'√® una buona notizia che mi permette di conferire a queste RAM l\'ambito premio di "miglior RAM RGB". Al contrario delle Kingston, queste potete programmarle una volta con iCue e poi disinstallarlo per sempre, e le RAM manterranno il profilo che avrete impostato a vita! Baster√† andare su "impostazioni hardware" dentro iCue, impostare i colori o l\'effetto psichedelico che pi√π si addice alla vostra cameretta, et voila, potrete disinstallare iCue per sempre, riavviare il computer, fare il boot in Linux, installare le RAM in un nuovo computer, saranno sempre illuminate con le impostazioni che avete scelto dentro iCue la prima volta.Non come le Kingston Fury che ad ogni avvio ritornano in modalit√† arcobaleno epilettico e non riprendono le impostazioni finch√© non caricherete Windows e il relativo servizio in background che le imposta. Poi ok, le Kingston si programmano tramite un tool di pochi Mb, che usa un servizio che gira in background in Windows anche lui che occupa una decina di Mb in RAM, molto molto meglio di iCue e i suoi 3.5Gb su disco di chiss√† cosa, ma comunque, non avere nulla che gira in background e il profilo che rimane direttamente memorizzato nell\'hardware √® sempre e comunque preferibile.Solo per questo, fermo restando che dei timings e delle velocit√† ce ne possiamo sbattere, le posso consigliare rispetto alle Kingston Fury.Un\'ultima cosa interessante di queste che ho notato, √® che hanno il sensore della temperatura. Quando le ho testate con Memtest86 per verificare che non fossero state rivendute difettate da Amazon Seconda Mano (perch√© fidarsi √® bene, non fidarsi √® meglio), anche la temperatura era visualizzata, prima volta nella mia vita che vedo delle RAM con sensore di temperatura attivo e funzionante. Molto bello peccato che non serve a nulla, perch√© anche dopo 4 ore intense di martellamenti da parte di Memtest86, la temperatura ha variato dai 30 ai 35C senza mai eccedere i 40. Ampiamente entro le raccomandazioni di utilizzo del produttore.Per concludere, sono delle normali RAM "da gaming" col dissipatore, che fanno il loro lavoro e si illuminano con effetti carini. I timings e le frequenze sono nella norma per il 99.9% degli utilizzi. Se vi interessano i led, queste o la variante 3200CL16 sono le migliori per il semplice fatto che le potrete impostare una volta e poi disinstallare l\'odioso software di Corsair per sempre (cosa che non si pu√≤ fare con le Kingston Fury). Le consiglio senza riserve, specialmente se le trovate allo stesso prezzo o meno rispetto ad altre, in generale comprate quelle che costano meno.', "La Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro SL 32 Go est absolument exceptionnelle en mati√®re de performance et d'esth√©tique. Son RGB est brillant et personnalisable, offrant une touche d'√©l√©gance √† mon setup. La vitesse de 3600 MHz associ√©e √† une latence de C18 assure une r√©activit√© et une rapidit√© incomparables, surtout lorsqu'il s'agit d'optimiser mon Ryzen 5 5600x. Le fait qu'elle fonctionne √† 1.35V signifie √©galement qu'elle est √©co√©nerg√©tique. Je suis vraiment impressionn√© par cette RAM et je la recommande vivement √† tout le monde.", "Le style est tr√®s sympa, l'xmp marche direct. Elle chauffe peut √™tre un peu plus que mes pr√©c√©dentes mais les performances sont bonnes", 'Como es bien sabido los productos Corsair suelen ser de muy buena calidad. En este caso las RAM van muy bien, son f√°ciles de instalar y son compatibles con software de personalizaci√≥n de color RGB con diferentes opciones. Da un toque muy chulo al pc adem√°s de dar un rendimiento muy bueno.', 'supporte XMP .RAS', 'I bought these needing an upgrade from 16gb. After half an hour of use i can definetly say there is some improvement! The RGB lights are bright and vibrant, and are nicely diffused. The iCue software is very janky though, and often freezes and doesnt change the lighting. I also had to go into the bios to change the ram speed to the supported 3200mhz. Installation was easy and took me no more than 5 minutes. Overall 9/10 best budget ram!', 'Perfecta calidad. Ni una queja de su rendimiento.', 'Tutto ok', 'Es hat Perfekt auf mein Board gepasst. Musste nur noch im BIOS die mhz anpassen. Bis jetzt gab es keine M√§ngel.']

Product: Corsair CS-CMW32GX4M2E3200C16 Vengeance RGB Pro 32GB (2 x 16GB) DDR4 DRAM 3200MHz C16 Memory Kit, Black
Reviews:
['gd', 'Pour l‚Äôinstant, rien √† dire, les 8 barrettes achet√©es sont fonctionnelles, et me permettent d‚Äôavoir 128 Go de RAM. Comme l‚Äôont dit certaines personnes dans les commentaires, il faut activer le profil XMP pour atteindre les 3200 Mhz sinon par d√©faut le syst√®me se base sur 2133 Mhz.Alors maintenant la question est : pourquoi 128 Go de RAM ? Eh bien dans mon cas √ßa me sert √† utiliser mon pc comme un serveur pour les jeux vid√©os et √† jouer en m√™me temps, √† g√©n√©rer des maps sur 7 Days to Die (environ 32 Go pour g√©n√©rer une carte, et si le pr√©-affichage est s√©lectionn√© en le plus haut, c‚Äôest environ 60-64 Go qui sont demand√©s), et √©galement √† utiliser plusieurs machines virtuelles en m√™me temps, en leur allouant une bonne quantit√© de RAM √† chacune pour √™tre tranquille.En dehors de √ßa, au vu du prix d‚Äôun processeur ou d‚Äôune carte graphique par exemple, le prix pay√© pour ces barrettes est assez bas en comparaison, donc tant qu‚Äô√† faire autant s‚Äôassurer d‚Äôavoir ce qu‚Äôil faut pour ne plus avoir √† y penser.(Petite note : j‚Äôai remarqu√© que pour les profils du logiciel iCUE, l‚Äôune des 8 barrettes n‚Äôavait pas prix la m√™me couleur d√©finie que les autres. Cependant, le switch de profil a instantan√©ment r√©gl√© le probl√®me. Je pense que c‚Äôest d√ª au fait que le pc a tellement de choses √† charger √† l‚Äôallumage qu‚Äôil est possible qu‚Äôil y ait un loup√© de temps en temps. √áa, ou alors il s‚Äôagit d‚Äôun petit bug)', "Barrette de RAM de chez corsaire en 3200 C16. ne pas oublier de d√©bloquer le profil dans le BIOS pour profiter du maximum de la fr√©quence.contr√¥le du RGB avec l'application corsaire ICUE. de couleur blanche parfaite pour compl√©ter une config en blanc.Bon produit.", "Produit conforme, tant qu'on n'oublie pas d'activer le profil XMP depuis le BIOS bien s√ªr, sinon on ne profite pas des MHz indiqu√©.", 'Das CORSAIR VENGEANCE RGB PRO 32GB (2x16GB) DDR4 3200 hat meine Erwartungen √ºbertroffen und ist ein absoluter Game-Changer f√ºr mein PC-Setup.Die Leistung dieses RAM-Moduls ist herausragend. Sie ist mit den meisten g√§ngigen Motherboards kompatibel und l√§sst sich einfach in bestehende Systeme integrieren.Insgesamt bin ich von dem CORSAIR VENGEANCE RGB PRO 32GB DDR4 3200 RAM begeistert. Product: G.Skill Ripjaws V Series 32GB (2 x 16GB) 288-Pin SDRAM (PC4-28800) DDR4 3600 CL16-19-19-39 1.35V Dual Channel Desktop Memory Model F4-3600C16D-32GVKC
Reviews: ["Bought these to go with my MSI Z490 Tomahawk + Intel I9 10850k for my new PC build. RAM speed started at 2133MHz, but after changing the settings in BIOs to use the correct XMP profile it is now running at its advertised speed of 3600MHz. There was more RAM clearance than I thought since I was initially considering NH-D15 + Corsair LPX but swapped to Dark Rock Pro 4 + G.Skill V instead. Didn't need to adjust the cooler fan at all.One thing that bothered me after receiving it was that the packaging for the RAM was not sealed with tape or adhesives which made me worried whether or not it was genuine. Not sure if it that is how its supposed to be packaged, but since installing I have not seen anything off to suggest that it is not genuine.", 'Cost effective dual-rank RAM that works on AMD B550 board.', "Good value RAM that simply works with Zen 3 CPU. I'm using ASUS X570 itx board.", 'Funciona perfecto con mi Ryzen 5800x en mi b350 con el perfil xmp habilitado, pero lo m√°s importante, es que es dual rank, no estoy cien porciento seguro de que todos los lotes de este modelo sean dual rank, no lo hab√≠a comprado por eso, as√≠ que result√≥ ser un bonus. Mi kit viene con chips hynix CJR por si alguien est√° interesado.', "I have two identical machines I built using an AMD 5600X and 32Gb of same memory except the first had a higher latency and never would reach the 3600 DRAM Speed.  I did not want to go down that rabbit hole overclocking just to see the rated 3600.  The RAM I bought for that first machine was listed as compatible and it was if you wanted to run it slower.  This recent RAM is fast and no problems with the msi B550 MAG Tomahawk and AMD 5600X and running the 3600 simply making one selection.  End of Aug I plan on buying another 32GB same RAM for that first machine and I'll use the slower memory in one of my two AMD 3600s", "Pop in, configure in BIOS and you're set.Haven't had any issues so far with this RAM, had to buy in a rush as a replacement for my old ones from Corsair, but they've become a permanent fix.", 'To start, my specs, in case if you are wondering if it will work with your system.Ryzen 7 3700XAsus TUF X570 Plus WiFiI got this set to replace my old RAM, which was two sets of mismatched sticks. Ive found that 16GB just isnt quite enough to run well for all of what I want to do at once on my system. I just kind of auto-specced the old sticks, and it turned out to run at 3200Mhz CL22, which is not great.All I needed to do was shove the two sticks in the #2 slots on my board, then tell my system in BIOS to use the XMP profile. Booted no problem, tested with some basic benchmarking, and no problems with stability.As to what is under those heat sinks, it looks like its dual rank Hynix CJR modules (which I understand is pretty good for enthusiast overclocking). XMP at CL 16-19-19-39 is very stable from what I can tell. I am just going to keep it at XMP for the time being and call it a day personally.Original July 2022Edit August 2022:Ive had a chance to try and manually tune the sticks for better performance. The original stock XMP is 16-19-19-19-39. I tried to set the sticks to 16-18-18-18-38 and I am able to boot the system (after some auto-training done by my mobo), however, the system becomes unstable and crashes within an hour or two, especially if I do something intensive. It looks like the sticks I got are unable to be tuned for any improvement at all. Its rock solid at the stock XMP settings though. I confirmed its fine via some memory benchmarking, along with just using my system for both gaming and other everyday tasks for multiple days with no issues related to RAM at all. I did also manage to run Memtest86 at stock XMP, and I can confirm that the set of sticks I got are in perfect order, no errors at all (which is expected of brand new sticks).Edit: End of August 2022:I have to change my score from 5 to 3 because I did some troubleshooting with my system. Ive had issues in the past with RAM and compatibility with my 3700X. I noticed that I am getting random shutdowns out of the blue of my entire system. The behavior is eerily similar to when I was having issues with RAM timings before. I updated my BIOS for my mobo to the most recent version, it did help with some stability, at least for gameplay, but I dont think it helped with my stability with my RAM. After messing with a bunch of things, it looks like its the DOCP/XMP profile for the RAM. The 16-19-19-39 at 3600Mhz is too much for the memory controller on my 3700X. Zen 2 is known for having issues with RAM compatibility and stability. To avoid random shutdowns, I am now just running the sticks at the default JDEC base spec, 2133Mhz. I did find that it seems to run OK at 3200Mhz C22 (with my mobo auto setting the timings). At this point, I am fed up with my 3700X. The issues with RAM are infuriating. I have a 5800X3D in the mail right now. I am hoping that Zen 3 has had their memory controllers improved significantly over Zen 2 so I can finally just set XMP and call it a day. As a side note, AMD is not the only one that has had issues with memory controllers of their CPUs (AMD 3000 series is known for problems with high frequency DDR4), Intel has recently been found to have problems too (Intel 12th gen is having problems with high frequency DDR5). This pair of sticks is shown to be compatible with my mobo and CPU combo by both G.Skill and Asus officially, but it seems like AMD dropped the ball with some very weak memory controllers on their 3000 series CPUs (they also got in trouble with over-advertising their clock frequencies for the 3000 series), so, if you are getting this for a 3600, 3700X, 3900X, etc, be wary, there isnt a guarantee it will work with absolutely no problems. I may update later on how these sticks of RAM are like with a 5800X3D in my TUF X570 Plus WiFi. I am relegating my 3700X to be used in the future for a home server PC and pairing it with a B550 board and some pedestrian 3200Mhz DDR4.', 'Worked flawlessly out of the packaging, nice and easy!', "This review is for G.Skill Ripjaws V Series 32GB (2 x 16GB) 288-Pin SDRAM (PC4-28800) DDR4 3600 CL16-19-19-39 1.35V Dual Channel Desktop Memory Model F4-3600C16D-32GVKCIm running it with a Ryzen 3900x and MSI X570s MPG Carbon Max WiFiI was looking to upgrade from 16GB to 32GB due to Diablo 4 hogging to much memory, and this really did the trick. Difference was night and day. Reviews:
["Overall I am very happy with this purchase and I enjoy using this.Why happy with the purchase:It works with my motherboard I bought in 2016, more like I am relieved it works. When I first installed it, my computer refuse to boot and entered a boot loop. I tried changing back to my older pair of ram and it still didn't work. So I had to hard reset the bios by removing the battery. I found out that it is because I used the XMP profile previously so it somehow tries to applies on this set of ram.Lesson learnt: Disable XMP profile before replacing rams.Why enjoy using this:It is because of the SDK and software. That's it.RGB effects are cool and all but it is still kind of plain and the audio visualizer is locked behind a Corsair audio product requirement. So I took the chance to program my own Rainbow Wave plus audio beats combo. Best of all the sample compiles with not much issue and easy to learn. It is much better than the RGB Fusion sdk.Note: Do not put CorsairGetLedPositionsByDeviceIndex in a loop thread or the memory usage will keep increasing.The iCUE dashboard also tracks the temperatures of most of the PC components including the graphics card. You have to enable the hard drive widget in the dashboard settings.", "Apr√®s maintenant 2 semaines d'utilisation je suis satisfait de cette achat.
