Des BSOD aux bouts de quelques dizaines de minutes avec erreurs diff√©rentes √† chaque fois.Du coup, apr√®s check si le probl√®me venez d'autres parts que la RAM (config bios, ou autres); un petit Memtest pour voir si ca viens de la RAM en elle-m√™me, et effectivement plus de 8000 erreurs sous Memtest d√®s la phase 2 des tests (sur 10). Je me suis r√©sign√© √† faire une demande de remplacement + renvoi de l'ancien kit.Le surlendemain, nouveau kit install√©; tout fonctionne √† merveille √† pr√©sent (plus aucune erreur sous Memtest).Concernant le RGB en lui m√™me, c'est tr√®s joli comme effet! (pour ceux qui aime √ßa). Vous pouvez personnaliser les effets via iCUE (software de Corsair). Si vous avez d√©j√† un p√©riph√©rique Corsair, la RAM est d√©tect√© sans aucune manipulation comme un p√©riph√©rique √† part enti√®re.Pour information: les deux kit sont √©quip√©s de puces SK Hynix.Je retire 1 √©toile pour le premier kit d√©fectueux, sinon c'est du 5/5 pour le second et son envoi rapide par Amazon.", 'Pour moi Corsair reste le "must" dans la m√©moire DDR4(DDR,DDR2,DDR3 etc) mais la ils font fort avec les Dominator Platinum RGB ! Jai achet√© il y a 2 semaines un kit de 2x8go de Vengeance RGB pour avoir 32 go mais 1 semaine apr√®s j'achetais un kit de 2x8Go de Dominator PLATINUM RGB en 3000mhz,que du bonheur tant niveau performances, qualit√© et RGB car elles sont param√©trables de A a Z ! De plus, je les fais OC √† 3800mhz en changeant les timings,z√©ro plantage,et ne chauffe pas plus de 42¬∞ ! Alors oui elles font RGB et tout le monde n'aime pas mais il en faut pour tout les go√ªts et concernant l'oc ce sont les meilleurs ! Du coup recommand√© 2x8go 3000mhz pour avoir 32go au total et pour avoir de plus bel effet RGB avec 4 barrettes.Par contre,Amazon, √©vitez de prendre DHL pour les livraisons car de 1 il ne livre pas le samedi (alors que livraison erait pr√©vue samedi) et de 2 le colis √©tait partiellement ouvert (inadmissible !!!!!),d√©√ßu de DHL, je sais d'Amazon n'est pas responsable mais √©viter ce transporteur car 0/10 point√© üò°', 'I ran a 8086k at 5Ghz using an AIO water cooled 280mm Radiator to support overclocking 4 sticks of these in an asus x Maximus formula. (Bought them 2 DIMM at a time)When running just the two 8GB sticks, XMP enabled and to their 19CL at 4000Mhz there were no problems for a year using default profiles. Some odd BSOD once in a while. Since these were applied on my daisy chain DIMM slot motherboard, using 4 of these together provided some challenges but correct voltage increase were applied to solve them, at the cost of heat increase.Samsung-die likes room temperature (20C), even while using their Corsair provided 4DIMM RAM fan at max speed, 4 of these guys ran at 31C while overclocked to their listed CAS timings at 4000Mhz passing mostly all tests, memtest86, AIDA64, at DRAM of 1.35v, VCCIO, VCCSA at around 1.3v, Unfortunately there is a consistent single row failure in memtest86‚Äôs 13th test, the hammer drop test. Where instabilities were due to going to 4000mhz and ironically creating kernel exploits while IMC interference could not be stopped due to the clockspeed.Nothing really to put here, these aren‚Äôt ECC and I‚Äôm not a RAM OC expert but I managed to go 17-21-21-38 before failing windows, probably due to IMC temperatures. I‚Äôll revisit this once I try out water cooling someday. But first I must delid my CPU and reapply liquid metal with the AIO and see how it goes. Good luck RAM overclockers.', "I added it the the additional two available memory slots on my motherboard, to bring my PC's overall memory up from 32GB to 64GB RAM.The RGB lighting on the memory modules are also quite cool and give my old PC a new space-age look.Wishing it were like about $150 cheaper than the 300 bucks that I paid for it though.For, being older memory - running at 3000Mhz - the price is way too high.", "I use my PC mainly for daily home office type of activities.  I do have a couple of games that I toy with every now and then, but gaming is not my main activity.  The memory installed without issue and the RGB lights lit up with a very nice waterfall type of light activity.  I had planned to get the Corsair iCue software to control the lights but have not done that yet.When I wanted to use the XMP profile, I had to put in the numbers by hand - as just turning on XMP crashed my system - using the numbers on the memory and not the XMP listing.  That worked and I plan to tighten the numbers up a little more.  I did see a 4 degree rise in temperature but think that is because I had to up the voltage to the needed 1.35V from my previous usual of 1.20V.  So instead of running at 34 degrees Celsius, I'm running about 37-38 degrees C.  I'm not done tinkering yet but the memory is a great addition to my PC.  And I love the night show.  The light are quite bright so I hope you don't sleep in the same room as your computer!", 'Ho acquistato 4 banchi di ram da 8 gb per non lasciare spazi vuoti sulla mia scheda madre, in versione 3000Mhz.Le ram si presentano in un packaging molto ben curato, da subito si capisce che si avr√† a che fare con un prodotto premium.La costruzione √® impeccabile, gran parte della struttura superiore √® in metallo, sono presenti dei led rgb sul lato superiore. I led possono essere controllati attraverso iCUE, il software messo a disposizione di Corsair, il quale √® assolutamente ben congegnato e stabile. Le prestazioni sono ottime, in linea con la qualit√† del prodotto.Forse costano qualcosa in pi√π rispetto ad altre ram, ma si ha a che fare con un prodotto davvero eccellente sia dal punto di vista costruttivo che  prestazionale.Consigliate ad occhi chiusi, piuttosto aspettate di pi√π se sono fuori budget, ma non lasciatevele sfuggire (ovviamente √® importante tenere sotto controllo il prezzo, talvolta questo scende di qualche decina di euro a seconda del modello).']

Reviews: ['', 'Package was well packaged and receivedStraight forward installation, update the ram with Icue Software. Everything works', "The RAM works as per you expect. Running with my Ryzen 3600 and my Asrock B550m Pro4 at 3600mhz using the XMP profile. No extra fiddling required, just set the XMP profile in BIOS and I was running at the advertised speed. Gotta use the Corsair iCUE software if i want the RAM's RGB lighting to shut off when my computer goes to sleep, or else they will remain lit until the computer shuts down.However, Singaporean buyers beware! Although this is sold by Amazon.sg and is from Singapore, it does not offer any local distributor warranty. Confirmed this with Convergent (Corsair's local distributer here in SG) myself.  So you dont get the usual conveniences, ie. :- Distributor sending your RAM for repair overseas for free.- 1 for 1 Exchanges- Loaning of RAM while your RAM is being repaired overseas.Something to be aware of as there is other Corsair RAM being sold on Amazon.sg that does come with local distributor warranty from Convergent and comes with the sticker on box to prove it. Just not this listing.Hope this helps someone.", 'If you cant find Samsung B-dies this is the best bet. Micron E dies are underrated and honestly a steal imo in terms of value/performance.Great stuff for the price. 3600 easily with DOCP or Ryzen Dram Calculator timings. Also possible to do 3800mhz w/some tweakingRam itself sits pretty high so clearance for top mount radiators may be an issue depending on case/size.RGB adjustment/sync requires Cosair iCUE software installation.', 'Works great at 3600mhz with my ryzen 5 3600 and b450 mortar max motherboard. RGB is also eye catching and works well with the mystic light software.', 'Have been purchased this 3 sets in single order placed in Jul22. Envelope sealed and inside boxes were sealed. Now in Aug22 purchased again but single set and received the package envelope sealed but the box not sealed. A bit disappointed...', 'When I opened the package, the seal on the box was already broken.Went to test the ram sticks, my PC wont boot.After hours of testing realized that one of the ram sticks is faulty sometimes it will boot sometimes it wont.Tested the ram sticks individually.Super pissed off.Item seems pre-owned or returned faulty then sold to me again...', "The Corsair Vengeance RGB PRO 16GB DDR4 3600MHz memory has taken my PC performance to a whole new level, and I couldn't be more thrilled with this upgrade. This memory kit not only boasts impressive technical specifications but also adds a touch of mesmerizing RGB lighting to my desktop setup.First and foremost, the performance of this memory kit is outstanding. With a capacity of 16GB (2x8GB) and a blazing-fast speed of 3600MHz (PC4-28800), my system experiences a significant boost in multitasking capabilities and overall responsiveness. Whether I'm running memory-intensive applications, gaming, or content creation, the Corsair Vengeance memory handles it all with ease.The sleek and elegant design of the memory modules perfectly complements my PC's aesthetics. The all-black heat spreaders exude a sense of sophistication, and the inclusion of RGB lighting takes it to a whole new level. The customizable RGB lighting can be synchronized with other Corsair components using their software, creating a harmonious and visually stunning light show.Installation was a breeze thanks to the user-friendly design. The memory modules fit securely into my motherboard's slots, and the heat spreaders effectively dissipate heat, ensuring stable and reliable performance even during extended usage.Corsair's commitment to quality shines through with this Vengeance RGB PRO memory. The memory modules undergo rigorous testing to ensure optimal performance, stability, and compatibility. I have complete peace of mind knowing that my investment is protected by Corsair's industry-leading warranty and customer support.Another advantage of this memory kit is its compatibility with both Intel and AMD platforms. I didn't have to worry about compatibility issues with my AMD-based system, and it worked flawlessly right out of the box.Additionally, the Corsair iCUE software provides intuitive control over the RGB lighting and allows me to synchronize the lighting effects with other Corsair RGB components, creating a unified and mesmerizing visual experience.In conclusion, the Corsair Vengeance RGB PRO 16GB DDR4 3600MHz memory is an absolute powerhouse that has elevated my PC's performance to new heights. Product: Crucial Ballistix RGB 3600 MHz DDR4 DRAM Desktop Gaming Memory Kit 16GB (8GBx2) CL16 BL2K8G36C16U4WL (White)
Reviews: ["The rams plastic packaging was torn open. The two plastic sealed point was ripped apart. It would take a lot of force to ripped apart those 2 seal point. Thankfully the rams works at the advertised speed under XMP 2.0 profile. But I had a hard time getting the RGB to sync. Crucial MOD utility doesn't work at all. After many tries, I got the Asus software to sync it finally.", 'Worked out of the box with xmp profile set to 3600mhz on my B450 + Ryzen 5600X.The software to control the lighting was completely bugged though. Would not open on my windows 10 system.', 'Works good, bought it at a lower price. RGB could be synced with my Asus motherboard using Armory Crate', 'I got this for my first build, a pink/white themed pc. Looks really nice with the white fans I got and cables through cablemod. Adds a nice touch to the pink', "Got this in prep for a Ryzen 5600X upgrade in a few month when prices come down. Was able to hit the XMP profile on first boot.Neutral Side: No real performance increase on a R2600, over 3200c16 Corsair sticks they are replacing, but I expect this to change with the better memory manager on the 5600X... I also didnt mess with timings yet, but I expect to be able to tighten up timings a bit after some effort.The down side:I do not like the MOD software... at all. I dont like loading it at startup, and I dont like the resource hit while its running... even if it's just 1% with dram LED synching off. and I reeeaaaaalllly dont like the LED animation code.I might have to make my own animations. I have a little experience with sk6812 and WS2812 drivers... but that's a whole other adventure.PS XPG had some of the nicest stock LED animations I have seen... I just couldnt get it to work at XMP speeds on a b550 MB... weird right?-Ryzen 2600 (no OC)-MSI B550M Bazooka (latest BIOS 01-04-2021)Over all I like them.EDIT: I can not get 4 sticks to hit XMP2 on my MB (3600c16). However 2x8 is stable at 3600c15/17/15/52. AND 4x8 3200c14 is stable and I get amazing performance.With 2x8GB @ 3600c16, r2600 CPU score on Time Spy is around 5900. At 4x8GB @ 3200c14 Time Spy is 6150ish with a fclk/uclk of 1:1.So far I'm happy", "Have just used this RAM in a RGB overkill build for a family member.The RAM itself is great, really good price for 3600 CL16 RGB RAM.Worked exactly as expected and the motherboard immediately got it running at 3600 via its XMP profile.However one of the key points of this RAM is the RGB function, which is honestly very good, it's quite bright and has plenty of options and control BUT the crucial MOD utility was very hit or miss.I was unable to control the RGB via MSI mystic light software or openrgb.Basically getting the RAM to work correctly on startup was next to impossible and it took a lot of fiddling. Kept giving a motherboard not recognised error.We did get it working in the end, no idea how or why but it just started working and it.I'm sure it might just be us in the minority so I haven't let the review rating be impacted too much as it honestly is great RAM but in future builds i might stick to corsair RGB RAM as the icue software is much better.", "Bought these to pair with a Ryzen 5 3600 as part of an upgrade, was looking for fast ram as I know Ryzen when tuned correctly can take advantage of it's speed. Initially just put them in and set the XMP 2.0 profile at 3600 at rated 16-18-18-18 timings, it worked as it should. And then I got curious!Using Ryzen memory calculator I started to experement, firstly these dimms are Micron E-die important if you are to get the right timings in the calculator, the rest is platform dependent.So I have tired 3600 at 16-14-14-14-36 All goodAlso 3733 at 15-20-15-15 36 all goodNow set on 3800 at 16-20-16-16-38 Again all goodYou also have to have to change the finer settings and set your voltages etc, but these dimms play ball unlike some others I have had. Ryzen is all about bandwidth and throughput, the fater the ram , the faster it will go.My 3600 is OC'd via the PBO in the bios and single core boost overriden to 200Mhz so it is boosting to 4.4Ghz on single thread work and mainly at 4.3Ghz in between paired with this Ram at the stated speeds it flies. Oh and the ram looks good too.", "as some people stated, the rgb resets back to rainbow everytime you shut down. not when in sleeping mode. they also said that the software for it ( MOD) was bad but in my experience, it was the easiest rgb setup i've ever had.. you can also make it start on startup wich just means you'll have a rainbow effect for a couple seconds. the ram is blazing fast and XMP ready for my ryzen build so there's that. last thing is, as some guy said, these are single rank so you would need 4 sticks to achieve dual channel for ryzen builds. i got 2 of these 3600mhz 16 gb (2x8gb) for a total of 32gb and it runs perfectly fine at the speed it was meant to. good product even at 140$ each kit but better if on sale. cheers", "Honeslty, it's crucial ballistix RAM. A pretty well known brand and line of memory modules that function well just fine. There's nothing crazy about the speed, but it's always good bang for the buck. I really don't have much negative to say about the consistency of the RAM.But, I purchased the RGB version, and the RGB doesn't want to be addressed. I have the ASRock B550m Pro4. Turns out there's a known problem with the MOD application for about the past year. For it to work, download the ASUS Armory application and control it through there.", "Nulla da dire sulle prestazioni della RAM, ma la gestione dei led lascia parecchio a desiderare. Il programma MOD presente sul sito del produttore √® abbastanza buggato, non ripristina le impostazioni dei led all'avvio e non mantiene la sincronizzazione tra i banchi. Alla fine ho gestito il tutto tramite programma di MSI, ma quello non permette di regolare la luminosit√† se non impostando un colore fisso. Insomma: funzionali ma si poteva fare meglio."]

Product: Crucial BL2K8G32C16U4W Ballistix 3200 MHz DDR4 DRAM Desktop Gaming Memory Kit, White, 16GB (8GBx2)
Reviews: ["I ordered 2 orders of 8*2 GB ram a few months ago, but this is actually not advisable as 8*4 GB rams are supposedly tested to work together (Same brand and same model are not guaranteed to work as a set, which is why you get 8*4 GB options). Please take note of this point.OverviewProduct received: Single Rank E-die 8GB rams at 3600 mhz and the stated XMP specs.Product defects: Yes, 2 sticks of ram.Product prices: Reasonable and cheaper when I bought it, but not worth as of 10/05/2021. Only buy this product if it is cheaper compared to local alternatives by 25 SGD.Product warranty: Cannot be RMAed to amazon SG after 4 months, only to original manufacturer in US after. I am uncertain if it can be sent back within a shorter period of time (one month) to amazon, but Crucial sent the replacement quickly.Review:Recent usage of my PC showed artifacts and I tested with memtest86 and TM5, separately and together on different ram slots. It took half a day to check and I discovered two sticks of ram with errors, with one having more errors than the other.Amazon SG doesn't handle RMA when I checked with them and I eventually contacted Crucial on their website, and mailed the faulty rams back to US which cost me around 13 SGD. A replacement set was sent back pretty quickly with fedex intl priority, which is a great plus for this brand.When I bought the rams on May 2021, they cost 125.62 SGD, but the price has since inflated to 157 SGD as of 10/05/2021. If I compare it to amazon US now, the price is 69.99 USD (~100 SGD). Buying it from amazon US would save you more money than buying it from amazon SG even if you add in the shipping charges; take note of this point.On the issue of local prices, a Lazada SG seller sells the same crucial 3600 Mhz ram for 155 SGD, so if I'm to compare my original costs including RMAing my rams to US, I still saved a few dollars, more if you actually purchase from Amazon US.In conclusion, I rate this product 4/5. There were defects but warranty was honored and replacement ram was sent back quickly and everything was resolved in approximately two weeks.", 'Though I have initial difficulty to install these dram, at the end i managed to install them and get the PC working. These RAMS are compatible to my motherboard ASUS TUF Z270 although they are not shown in the crucial page.', 'Fast delivery. Estimated date was on 21 November. But it came earlier than that. Thank you so much. This is great! (edit) Just to add on, I managed to test the waters to overclock it until 3800mhz with 1900mhz FCLK. Then I‚Äôm assuming the rest would just be a black screen because I‚Äôve tested above 3800mhz and it doesn‚Äôt boot.', "Love the red colour and the form factor.  Purchased it as an upgrade from the previous 2133Mhz to 3200Mhz.  Somehow only achieved a 3000Mhz RAM speed.  Perhaps it's my mobo and CPU.  Overall, a great purchase!", "Awesome product for it's cost. Used this for a few of my SFF builds.", 'Working great on ryzen 5 3600 with XMP on. Running at 3600MHz with no issue so far. I have got a mortar max for the motherboard. Probably will buy another kit to make it 32gb when the price goes down.', 'what more can you ask for? though ddr4 prices are still around the high side. could have gotten a 32gb dual rank sticks 1.5 years ago', 'Exquisite items like this could max.', 'Dual stick single rank RAM at 3600MHz XMP. Packaging was not fancy but works quite easily.', 'Good value for money, works well. Just remember to enable xmp in the BIOS']

Reviews:
['Received my item in good working condition.', 'Thanks to Amazon.  This memory is difficult to source locally.  Once slotted in the motherboard and run windows everything is fine, albeit with a few tweak since certain window such as win 7 cannot recognise in excess of 8GB ram.', 'Replaced older sticks in an old pc. Slotted them in and was detected by bios no problem. Running Windows 10 with Biostar H67 mobo.', 'Hi I bought this to add into old MacBook Pro but not compatible. I want to return and buy a new one which is compatible with Mac book pro mid 2011 . Would you help to exchange or refund? Preferably if I can have an exchange so that I don‚Äôt need to search .', 'üëç', 'M√©moire fiable sans probl√®me bonne rapidit√©. Le prix et un peu haut', 'I install it and works  good', 'super!', "Good RAM when it works....both sticks failed oddly at the same time within the 2 years guarantee so returned it ...a simple process that Amazon decided to overcomplicate and 'lose' the return.", 'Update (10/28/15): It has now been three years since I installed two pairs of these memory modules in my home-built computer (4 DIMMS, for a total of 32 GB). The memory has operated flawlessly.I installed four of these memory modules in my new computer. They are working just fine. I ran a (self-repeating) memory test for over 24 hours prior to loading the operating system.Before you order memory modules, you should review the webpage and "User Guide" for your motherboard. I recently built a new computer using the\xa0
ASUS Maximus V FORMULA LGA 1155 Intel Z77 Extended ATX DDR3 2800 PCIe 3.0 HDMI SupremeFX IV Audio Motherboard
. The ASUS website (quite conveniently) provides a Qualified Vendor Lists (QVL) of compatible memory for this motherboard (although it may not be up-to-date for 8GB modules). Your motherboard's vendor may have a similar list.If you purchased a ready-built computer, then look on the manufacturer's website to verify that you are purchasing the correct memory. For example, if you purchased your computer from the biggest computer maker, then log-on to your account, enter the Service Tag number for your computer, and then find the memory requirements. Or, you could just call and ask.My computer's motherboard requires (1.5 volt) DDR3 dual in-line memory modules (DIMMs), installed in "matched sets" for "dual channel" function. My motherboard's "User Guide" recommends installing DIMMs from the same vendor, with the same CAS latency, and of the same version or date code (D/C). Because of this recommendations, and because these memory modules were ridiculously inexpensive when I bought them, I went ahead and installed the maximum memory of four 8 GB DIMMs (32 GB). You can buy this memory with one pair of DIMMs or two pairs of DIMMs:\xa0
Corsair Vengeance 16GB (2x8GB)  DDR3 1600 MHz (PC3 12800) Desktop Memory (CMZ16GX3M2A1600C10)
\xa0or\xa0
Corsair Vengeance 32GB (4x8GB)  DDR3 1600 MHz (PC3 12800) Desktop Memory (CMZ32GX3M4X1600C10)
.If you are interested in over-clocking memory, then you might want to research (1.5 volt) DDR3 DIMMs with higher clock ratings (i.e., 1866 MHz, 2000 MHz, 2133 MHz, and 2400 MHz). Naturally, I wanted the 2400 MHz memory; but I decided to try the much cheaper 1600 MHz memory first.Please note: If you are only installing two DIMMS, you may need to install them in only two specific slots on the mother board (i.e., you can't just install them in any two slots). Check the "User Guide" for your motherboard to ensure that you are inserting the DIMMs in the correct slots. Of course, if you fill all slots with "matching" DIMMs, this will not be a concern.No matter how much physical memory you install, your copy of the Windows operating system may limit how much memory your computer can use. The 32 bit versions of Windows can only address a maximum of 4 GB of memory, with only (about) 3.5 GB of that usable.Windows 64 bit memory limits:- Windows 8 Professional: 512 GB- Windows 8: 128 GB- Windows 7 Professional or Ultimate: 192 GB- Windows Vista Ultimate: 128 GB- Windows 7 or Windows Vista Home Premium: 16 GB- Windows 7 or Windows Vista Home Basic: 8 GBLastly, I recommend that you run a memory test on your newly-installed memory. I used Memtest86+ (it's free). Extract the image (iso) file from the ZIP file, and then create a bootable CD by burning disc from image (do NOT copy the iso file to CD, burn disc from image). I ran this memory test prior to loading the operating system.']

Merci d'avance pour votre soutien !", 'These were a lot cheaper than the non-RGB version and were the only reasonably-priced high performance memory modules I could find listed as compatible with my Asus X590 Tuf Pro motherboard. The RGB caps work with the motherboard\'s Aura functionality which means I can change how the colours appear. The RGB functionality wasn\'t an important factor in choosing this item, but my PC\'s case has a TG side panel so I thought "why not" and saved about 20 quid thanks to Amazon\'s Black Friday deals.The only niggle is that they\'re not low profile and indeed I had to adjust the front CPU cooler fan on my Noctua NH-D15 upwards by about 10mm, which doesn\'t affect cooling performance noticeably. If your CPU cooler has only one central fan than there\'ll be plenty of clearance with these DIMMs.With my mobo I\'ve set the memory speed to 3200 though I\'ve read a review stating that they can be pushed to 4200 but are stable at 3600. I\'ve rated stability as a three because it\'s too early to tell, but I have run Passmark Memtest for about 4 hours of diagnostic tests which all passed.Recommended is your mobo/CPU cooler provide sufficient clearance at the front of the cooler.', "This ram is amazing, small form helps, and speed is good than my last ram. Einziger Kritikpunkt ist, dass sie nach einiger Zeit nicht mehr synchron laufen, was sich aber durch einen Neustart des Systems beheben l√§sst.Ich w√ºrde Ihn jeder Zeit wieder kaufen (wenn 32 GB nicht mehr reichen, kaufe ich den Gleichen noch einmal nach und lasse ihn im Quad-Channel laufen).', 'Will update the review as I literally just installed them, they work just fine and as it was my concern, they are picked up by Armoury Crate just fine and synch with the rest of my system no problem. I have a z370i from Asus with latest bios.Also saw some people who probably do not have a clue about PC, which is fine, but do your Google search. If you install them and the previous module was substantially different it may not post at all, not even in the bios, you just have to clear the cmos which is a 5 second job and then set your bios accordingly.If I come across any issue will update this, just turn them to 3600mhz (3200 model) and windows booted just fine.', "Ho acquistato queste RAM  ormai diversi mesi fa , e devo dire che fino ad oggi mi sono trovato molto bene per l'uso che faccio con il mio pc , il rapporto qualit√† prezzo nel mio caso √® stato ottimo perch√® ho comprato 2 da 16gb 3200mhz a soli 130 euro scontate , i led li controllavo tramite un app esterna che ho sincronizzato con gli altri led del mio pc , ed il risultato finale √® stato molto graditoSe ci sar√† qualche offerta vi consiglio di acquistarle , √® un ottimo prodotto", 'I have just finished my new gaming rig and this DDR4 RAM with RGB lights is a solid work horse. It looks gorgeous when in use and I can control light effects with my MSI X470 gaming plus max motherboard.  I had no issue with the RAM and system booted with XMP straight after I put all the components together.  It has been running very smoothly with AMD Ryzen 3600 and RAM temperature levels are less than 40¬∞C when under stress. It normally stays at 27¬∞C . 3200MHz is fast enough for my needs and I never over clock things but this RAM has plenty of potential for OC.Overall I am very satisfied with my purchase and I am happy to endorse 5 Stars rating.', "Recommended, i've been using these RAMs for more than 1 year and they are excellent, they work very well and they look great, i've seen people complaining about RGB, it's true, it can only be controlled with an APP of the brand, but not for that i put 2 rating stars in qualification... Product: GIGABYTE GP-ASM2NE6200TTT
Reviews: ['Great product, cheaper and faster', 'Performance in a budget', 'PS5 formatting only got 3879mbs read speed of the "7000" , when the console needs a minimum of 5500 to work.So wasted time installing it. Have to spend $$ to buy an external encasement to format it via a PC. With the new firmware updates. ....cuz yeh storage drives now need firmware updates to work right üëç', 'This is a lie say usb and it‚Äôs not, I return it', 'Sin problemas en con el disco.', 'Llego en el tiempo correcto y todo perfecto', 'This device [GIGABYTE AORUS] was easy to install for my PS5.  It is a Gen 4 SSD (which is the requirement for use of the expansion slot).  Fast, efficient, ESO Game transfer from the main console drive (136G) into the SSD only took about 2min and now operates as primary source for game play with faster than expected speeds. I am very happy with this product.', 'Update: I have been using this for about 7 months now and decided to do a Crystal Mark test. Well... the numbers speak for themselves.Bought this to pair with my Aorus x570 Elite. (so yes gen 4 can be utilized)Value for the money is horrible, it will not make you a better gamer, but really easy to install.I have a Crucial MX500 1TB SATA SSD and I see zero difference in loading games. So the SATA has turned into a game library since there is no performance difference. Transferring large files though is a different story, it is fast, and Acronis software that came with my Crucial SSD worked to clone my operating system on the this. It loads into windows super fast. My bios gives me like, 3 seconds to mash delete to get into bios, after that I am basically in windows. No waiting. I used to wait maybe 15-20 seconds to be completely in Windows. Now its like 8 seconds. It makes every other computer I use feel broken. If you have a special use case for this and have the money it is a great M.2. I only bought it because I have an X570 board, and what is the point of having one of these boards if you are not going to take advantage of PCIe Gen 4? I might buy the 500GB version for my operating system, transfer my game library to this 1TB, and use my Crucial SSD as a media folder.', 'Does not test no where near specs stated in ad!!!!!! Best read  speed I was able to obtain was 3800ish, no where near the 5000 or 5500 claimed in ad. Card did install very easy and ps5 was easy to set up. Data moved to it very quickly (71 gig moved in 2 minutes).very dissatisfied with false information in ad.. months later I have had 0 issues with it and works well. Raised rating because of that.', "I build for myself a performance PCmotherboard: TRX40 AORUS MASTERCPU: AMD Ryzen Threadripper 3960XMemory: corsair 128 GB DDR4 3200Graphic card during installation: AMD RX 580 8 GB.I tried to install Windows 10 OS on GIGABYTE AORUS NVMe Gen4 M.2 2TB with no success.I was able to install the OS, but it didn't boot, I tried by installing from a new bootable flash memory stick, I tried to install from a CD drive, and I even cloned an existing working M2 drive.Nothing worked, I called Amazon and they sent me a replacement.Before the replacement arrived I find out that the M2 is set as MBR partition, this can't support windows 10.I booted with other drive changed the partition to GPT, and everything working perfectly.while I was trying to find the issue I opened an incident with Gigabyte support, it's more than a month and they can't provide me with what to do, they keep asking me to re-install, they support team has no idea about the partiitiong.Recomandion to Gigabyte: no one will spend $550 on a PCI 4.0 M2 and install windows XP, stop using MBR partition if you want to keep do it, please provide the documentation and update your website.To summarize, good product, fast IO, looks good, and serve the purpose, recommended."]

Product: OWC 16Gb (2 X 8Gb) 1867 Mhz Ddr3 So-Dimm Pc3-14900 204 Pin Cl11 Memory Upgrade, (1867Ddr3S16P)
Reviews: ['An erster stelle bin ich verwundert √ºber die schnelle Lieferzeit.Gestern um 16:00 Uhr bestellt und am Folgetag zugestellt, erinnert mich stark an die anfangs Zeit von Amazon Prime.Mein iMac end 2015 l√§uft auf einmal so fl√ºssig wie neu.Ich bin wirklich verwundert das mein update von 8GB auf 24GB einen so gro√üen unterschied darstellt.Die Ladezeit ist √§hnlich zu meinem M1 MacBook Air und ich empfehle wirklich jeden ein solches RAM Speicher Upgrade.', 'O produto atendeu as minhas expectativas e melhorou o desempenho do meu IMac .', 'Best for i mac 27 retina ..amazing product.compatible and fast ...easy to install...', 'Come da descrizione perfetto compatibile mac', 'In early 2016 I bought my late 2015 iMac 27" Retina 5K with 8GB and a standard HDD. It was super fast running macOS Sierra, High Sierra, and Mojave. Then when I upgraded to Catalina, it went from flying to crawling. I suffered with it for years. Then recently I read something that suggested I needed more RAM. As a software engineer for decades, it seemed impossible to me that this iMac couldn\'t run decently with 8GB since it already had for 3 OS versions.  Anyway, I installed two OWC 8GB sticks to give me a total of 24GB and to my delight my iMac has been reborn, now as blazing fast as the day I got it. I have fallen in love again with my big beautiful iMac.I feel very dumb for not doing this years ago, but in my defense, despite my many interactions with Apple Care over the years, not a single tech suggested this simple fix.I\'m now running macOS Monterey and it\'s still super fast.', 'Worked perfectly', 'Parfect for my imac 2015', 'F√ºr mein IMAC 2015 super passt!', 'TOP', 'iMac„ÄÅ„É°„É¢„É™16G„Åß‰ΩúÊ•≠„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„Åü„ÇâÈ†ªÁπÅ„Å´Âãï‰Ωú‰∏çÂÆâÂÆö„Å´„Å™„Å£„Åü„Åü„ÇÅËøΩÂä†„É°„É¢„É™16G„ÅßÂêàË®à32GÂÆüË£Ö„Åß„ÄÇÂÆâÂÆö„Åó„Å¶Âãï‰Ωú„Åô„Çã„Çà„ÅÜ„Å´Êàê„Çä„Åæ„Åó„Åü„ÄÇHD‰∫§Êèõ„ÇÇËÄÉ„Åà„Åæ„Åó„Åü„Åå„ÄÅÂΩìÂàÜ„ÅÑ„Åæ„ÅÆÁä∂ÊÖã„ÅßÊßòÂ≠êË¶ã„Å´„Å™„Çä„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ']

It runs flawlessly at 4000 Mhz but will not run stable at 5200 Mhz as of right now with the current Asus BIOS software and can not run XMP profiles. My specs are the following:Asus TUF GAMING Z690-PLUS WIFI D4 LGA 1700Intel Core i7-12700K4x16 GB Corsair Dominator Platinum RGB DDR5 5200 Mhz C40EVGA Geforce RTX 2060EVGA Supernova 750 W 80 Plus GoldHope this helps.", "He hear people one here complaining about the LED's?  IF you case looks don't matter who cares about the led, if it does matter and you don't want them then turn them off; FOR THE LOVE OF ALL THATS HOLLY DON'T TAKE IT A PART like another clown suggested to remove the led's.The ram is fast this is my first DDR5 machine so hard to say if this DDR5 is better than others but my machine screams with 64gb of this ram and a 13900k.  The ram does work and sync with my Aura sync on my Z790 motherboard so for those that like matchy matchy led's this is for you.", 'A warnings about Intel DDR% memory.  There is a reason Corsair dont sell this RAM current in quad packs at 5600.  All current intel based Mobos are not able to consume reliably 4 DIMMS above 4000.  You can purchase 4x16 from Corsair (for example) but you will notice the speed is limited to less than 4000. Typically 3600. The issue is with ALL Intel based Mobos today (2022).So buyer beware. Use ONLY two DIMM if you want to achieve speeds above 4000.', 'I am a corsair junkie, so when I built my brand new custom, and finally upgrading from DDR3 to DDR5 I of course had to go with these dominators. Beautiful.', 'RAM is expensive at the time I bought this kit (¬£404), which is a joke for RAM! Regarding the speed of the RAM, I did not really notice any tangible difference when compared to my old DDR4 3600 RAM kit, this may be due to the higher latency.The RAM has been very stable and XMP on my MOBO (Aorus Z690 Master) gave me a chip manufacturer specific profile (Samsung 5600) to use, which worked flawlessly.I bought this kit as I had no choice, not realising that my board only supported DDR5 (I thought it was backward compatible stupidly), it was the first kit to come into stock, I am pleased to be future proofed (hopefully) but if budget was an issue, getting a DDR4 compatible board would be a much better way to go as these DDR5 sticks did not offer me much if anything by way of  performance increase over my old DDR4 and cost nearly twice as much.', 'Ho avuto qualche rarissimo caso di crash, ma tutto soommato vanno molto bene, diamo tempo a questa quinta gen di crescere']

Product: Kingston Fury Beast 32GB (2x16GB) 5600MHz DDR5 CL40 DIMM (Kit of 2) Desktop Memory KF556C40BBK2-32,Black
Reviews: ['Boosted my computing speed by a great lot!', 'Used onto my new build 12th gen Z690-G. After update BIOS then enable XMP in BIOS. Luckily no hiccup at startup.', 'Have been running the Dimms for last 2 months with no issues!', "La Kingston FURY Beast 32GB (2x16GB) 5600MT/s DDR5 CL40 DIMM √® una memoria fantastica per il gaming sui computer fissi. Ho acquistato questo kit che contiene due moduli da 16GB ciascuno, per un totale di 32GB di capacit√†. Questo mi permette di sfruttare la modalit√† dual-channel, migliorando le prestazioni complessive del mio sistema.La cosa pi√π impressionante di questa memoria √® la sua velocit√† di clock di 5600MT/s. √à davvero veloce e si traduce in un'esperienza di gioco super fluida e reattiva. Non ho mai avuto problemi di rallentamenti o lag durante le mie sessioni di gioco pi√π intense.Un'altra cosa positiva √® il profilo di latenza di 40 (CL40). Questo valore indica il tempo che la memoria impiega per rispondere alle richieste del processore. Pi√π basso √® il valore, migliori sono le prestazioni. Con un CL di 40, posso dire che questa memoria offre un buon equilibrio tra prestazioni e prezzo.Conosco Kingston come un marchio affidabile nel settore delle memorie, quindi sono sicuro che la FURY Beast DDR5 sia di alta qualit√†. √à costruita con componenti di ottima qualit√† e ha superato severi test di qualit√†, il che mi fa sentire tranquillo riguardo alla sua affidabilit√† a lungo termine.Mi piace anche il design del modulo. √à elegante e ha un dissipatore di calore nero che non solo sembra bello, ma aiuta anche a mantenere la memoria fresca durante le sessioni di gioco intense.Una cosa importante da tenere a mente √® che questa memoria √® compatibile solo con schede madri che supportano la tecnologia DDR5. Quindi, prima di acquistarla, assicurati che la tua scheda madre sia compatibile, altrimenti non riuscirai ad installarla correttamente.In conclusione, sono davvero soddisfatto della Kingston FURY Beast 32GB (2x16GB) 5600MT/s DDR5 CL40 DIMM. √à una memoria di alta qualit√† che offre prestazioni eccezionali per i giocatori pi√π esigenti. La sua velocit√† di clock elevata, il profilo di latenza ottimizzato e il design di alta qualit√† la rendono un'ottima scelta per tutti coloro che vogliono migliorare le prestazioni del proprio computer da gioco.", 'Bought 2 pieces when the price was extra low, cheaper than 2x kit.Works great on my Asus Prime Z690A with XMP (5200mhz) and Intel 12600kf OC @ 5.1ghz.', "Summary: I don't think you can go wrong with this memory.  Using in Dell XPS 17 9730.Pros: Fast, ReliableCons:  A little pricey, hard to get at this time in the US for some reasonDetail:  As anyone who is somewhat technically savvy knows when you buy a new laptop the manufacturers always overcharge for memory.  I find it's always much cheaper to buy the lowest amount you can for the laptop you can and replace with new memory right away.  You can literally throw the OEM memory away and buy new and same $100 or more in the process.  In this case I also went from 4800 to 5200 speed as well.  Why did it not register at 5600 like advertised you ask?  This is not Kingston's fault.  In my case it's because there is a known issue with Intel chipsets at 64GB of memory.  I knew this before buying and only expected to get 5200.  Not sure if AMD has this issue as well, but a lot of Intel based systems do, even the top of the line Alienware 18 as of the time of this review.Reseller:  I purchased this item from a reseller out of Texas who had a lot of negative reviews, most which Amazon defended due to manufacturer/supply chain issues.  My delivery was a few days late, but did make it. I was kind of expecting this ahead of time.  I found in my research that this memory isn't common and the reseller probably had to work overtime to get it from Kingston.  My guess is that it had to be imported.  If you find this review and are looking at the same reseller for this product, know that I believe he/she/they are truly trying to do a good job but are in some cases selling products like this that are often hard to get and that is why their reviews aren't all 5-star.", 'I already use a SSD with either Ryzen 5 or 7..  I say that because I was quite happy working with 8gig ram, and module was failing..  I splashed out on this, now I have noticed massive difference between then and with this 64gig pack..  amazing and required if you do anything intensive on computer from games to videos it can easily deal with your requirements.  As an aside I note windows is now fully working within the memory and that helps the whole process, I will absolutely buy this again for other machines as I plan to separate the games and music onto other machines...  Absolutely recommend', 'Headline says it all. This was so easy to OC I can hardly believe it, I just copied the Renegade timings and then improved on that.. Having sent the 2 x 8 sticks back due to slower x4 large chips I ordered the 32Gb set from the warehouse and will start with the secondary timings next.', "buone ram versione ddr5, veramente veloci ed efficaci. mancano di led o cose varie di abbellimento, ma a chi interessa l'efficienza e non l'estetica, le consiglio", 'Chegou em boas condi√ß√µes a caixa e estou usando a mais de um m√™s e sem o que reclamar at√© o momento, o pre√ßo tamb√©m est√° aceit√°vel se comparar com outras marcas que s√£o mais caras.']

Also good for an Intel i5-12400f as the clock speeds for DDR5 is limited to 4800mhz', "The media could not be loaded.
                



\xa0Im very happy with this Corsair DDR5-5200mhz memory. It looks great on my mostly white build PC and I have it running at 5400 via a user configurable XMP profile in my Gigabyte z690 aero D-BIOS.It was not obvious at first why it was running at 4800 and that I only seemed to have one XMP profile to set. but as I discovered you can have up to 3 xmp profiles once set under advanced memory settings and SPD (Gigabyte z690 aero D)I'm sure this memory can be run at a higher frequency but that will involve changing voltages and timings which can be troublesome if not done correctly, and the BIOS will have to be reset.You can check easily if you have the correct speed by going to Windows Task manager/Performance and Memory tab, or,download cpu-z app.I will purchase another 64bg of this memory to give me a total of 128gb for my system, which will be useful for vst libraries and video editing etc. But this will more than likely require adjusting voltages, etc, to get the required speed.Highly recommended.UPDATE.  I  bought another pair of these sticks (black) for a total of 128gbI got the 64gb Corsair DDR5-5200mhz kits in the black version for an excellent price; this was to add to my Corsair 64GB DDR5-5200mhz white kit for a total of 128gb for my system. I would have preferred the white version I previously bought for my PC build, but the black sticks were much cheaper than what I originally paid; it was a no-brainer.I have these sticks and the white ones in an MSI z790 edge wi-fi motherboard. I had a Gigabyte z690 D aero, with 64gb white set in my original review , but I had to get another motherboard for various reasons.With just two sticks in my motherboard I managed to get them running stable at 5400mhz. (XMP profiles), which was great, but when I added 4 sticks at 128gb, the fastest I could get was 4800mhz, that was both motherboards.However, Recently MSI updated their BIOS for this board which included fixes for better memory compatibility, so, I decided to try get 5200mhz running again, and to my surprise it worked perfectly, for a while. But, even after passing a memory test and playing a few games without any problems, I got a windows green screen error when I was closing down an app. So then, I decided to try and get at least 5000mhz running, which I have them running at now, stable. Actually, they are running at 5067mhz.I'm very happy with this speed and do not mind losing 200mhz from the speed they are supposed to run at. In fact, the speed difference when I had 64GB running at 5200 and beyond is actually quite negligible, according to various memory tests.Overall, I think this memory performs well and is from a top tier brand, which means better compatibility with motherboards. With future BIOS updates, perhaps 128gb might run at 5200 and beyond, stable,  here's hoping.Highly recommendedUPDATE 2.MSI released another BIOS update (7D91vH4) for my z790 wifi edge motherboard, which includes improved memory compatibility and many other updates. I updated it and adjusted the Dram frequency to 5200Mhz G2, while disabling the XMP profile, and it has been running stable while doing memory tests and playing games etc.My current system specs:I9-13900kMSI z790 wi-fi edgeGigabyte RTX 4070 aeroAsus Essence STX II sound cardKingston 1tb KC3000 PCIe 4.0 NVMe M.2 SSDArctic liquid freezer II 360 RGB AiOAnother 3 nvme drives and two ssd‚Äôs", 'Le memorie sono ottime, ho preso 4 banchi da 32gb per stare tranquillo un po‚Äô di anni. L‚Äôunico difetto, la scheda madre ASUS Prime Z690P le imposta a 4800mhz ed ho dovuto regolare manualmente i 5200mhz, ed il sistema rimane stabilissimo. Processore I7-13700K non overclockato, va benissimo con queste.', 'They work well. now I have 64 GB ram', 'Always had good quality from Corsair, this RAM worked without issue.', 'Excellent', 'Restituito perch√© incompatibile con la mia MB, servizio resi Amazon veloce, cortese, non c‚Äô√® niente da dire', 'Tras varios meses de uso debo decir que me parecen muy cumplidoras, sin ningun problema para ejecutar aplicaciones, y no me han presentado ninguna falla']

Product: Corsair Vengeance LPX 256GB (8x32GB) DDR4 3200 (PC4-25600) C16 1.35V Desktop Memory - Black
Reviews: ["Individual Desktop PC of 03 installed with the 32's, 64's & 128's GB capacities.", 'I\'ve been running these in my PC for about 6 months now. My PC is running at 128GB RAM very nicely. Bit fiddly installing it in, but that\'s just because I have a cooling pipe and fans right near where the RAM slots are, hence why I went for low profile RAM chips, otherwise I would have gone for RGB ones. Word of advice, make sure you choose the right XMP profile in the BIOS. The ones I bought are meant to be set to 3200MHz, I accidently set it to the 3600MHz profile. As you can imagine, it was unstable and crashed a couple of times. I went into the BIOS and realised I\'d set it to the wrong XMP profile...what a pillock lol! Since putting it on the correct XMP profile, it\'s ran like a dream, and I push my machine hard with editing and rendering very large video files. But yeah, other than my own "idiot moment," faultless!', 'What a great buy', 'No issues whatsoever. Using four of these for 128GB in a basic B660 board with XMP profile 1.  This profile raises the voltage to 1.35v and I set it back down to 1.2v.  Perfectly stable.  Have not tried overclocking.', "Was noticing that the browser was using quite a bit of memory, due to the number of tabs being open.  I like to keep the multiple tabs open, due to most of them being work related and I'll need to jump between all of them through out the day.  Of course, sometime everything became sluggish due to high mem usage.With the new 128gb of ram, haven't even made a dent in it, and no matter how many tabs I have open everything keeps running nice and smooth.", 'Does what it‚Äôs supposed to do.  I can run multiple windows, app‚Äôs, streams, etc. with no problem.  Glad I went with these!', 'Super ran nur leider wurde mir der falsche geliefert diese lief nur auf 3200mhz aber Amazon typisch wurde das super schnell gekl√§rt!', 'Working pretty good with my ASUS Z590-E GAMING WIFI and my Intel i9-11900K with the XMP profile enabled.Using mainly for video edition and gaming.', 'There are certain types of applications that require large amounts of homogeneous, contiguous memory to process the data, such a processing of gigapixel (and beyond) panoramic photos. I purchased this kit, which is the maximum my current CPU supports, and it worked without any issues. When I checked with Corsair whether I could (on an upgraded CPU) combine two kits (with same part number) to double the amount of RAM, the response was kind of "we can\'t support it because it hasn\'t been tested (as a combination)" and recommended I had to buy a another, 256GB kit.This suggests potential issues with the consistency/reliability of these memory kits when it comes to upgrading, which damages consumer confidence.Hence, I can recommend this kit if you don\'t ever plan to add more memory to your system.', 'Bought the 2x8 4000MHz kit, for the same price you get 2x16gb 3600MHz, which I think it a lot more value.']

Product: Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro 32GB (2x16GB) DDR4 2933 (PC4-23400) C16 Desktop Memory - Black PC Memory CMW32GX4M2Z2933C16
Reviews: ['Ram acquistata per fare un upgrade dalla memoria stock del mio PC da 16 GB a 32 GB, visto che ormai andava stretta per quello che faccio.La Ram funziona molto bene, ha un design accattivante ed √® perfetta sia in ambito Lavorativo, che per i Gamer. Personalmente non ho mai avuto problemi ne di Hardware, ne di Software dall\'installazione.Piccole note prima di parlare del prodotto:- Prima dell\'acquisto vi consiglio di controllare attentamente quanti MHz il vostro Processore e la vostra Scheda Madre riescono a supportare, in modo da evitare una spesa inutile per una Ram troppo potente, per esempio se il vostro processore supporta solamente 2667 MHz, prendere una Ram da 3600 MHz sar√† inutile in quanto verr√† automaticamente bloccata dal Bios a 2667 MHz, senza avere la possibilit√† di aumentarla. Stessa cosa per quanto riguarda la Scheda Madre;- Essendo che stiamo installando una nuova memoria, viene richiesto l\'update dal BIOS! Ma niente di preoccupante, in quanto possiamo trovare una miriade di video a riguardo, e fidatevi, √® pi√π facile a farsi che a dirsi.Per quanto riguarda la Ram invece:- La confezione √® molto semplice e fine, purtroppo senza la presenza di materiale protettivo tipo pluriball, per questo vi consiglio di farla spedire direttamente in un luogo dove potete ritirarlo sul momento oppure a un Amazon Locker, in modo da prevenire eventuali urti alla consegna;- I led sono modificabili attraverso un\'applicazione apposita chiamata iCUE che potete trovare direttamente sul sito della Corsair, dove potete essenzialmente sbizzarrirvi con i "Murals", che sono dei preset di colori ed effetti, oppure potrete creare i vostri personalizzati, anche in maniera individuale, quindi una Ram pu√≤ avere un effetto diverso rispetto all\'altra;- Parlando di prestazioni e temperature invece, questa sfrutta tutta la sua potenza e non supera mai i 55 ¬∞C, anche sotto sforzo, con i MHz impostati al massimo e con la presenza di un Overclock, probabilmente grazie al sistema di raffreddamento presente direttamente nella Ram.In alcuni videogiochi che sono Ram Hungry (utilizzano molta Ram) sono riuscito tranquillamente a guadagnare 20+ FPS, non c\'√® pi√π la presenza di scatti e tutto funziona in maniera molto pi√π fluida, anche avendo pi√π applicazioni aperte, compresi due programmi di Streaming contemporaneamente (OBS e lo streaming di Discord, per esempio)Per quanto riguarda invece programmi per lavoro tipo Photoshop oppure Illustrator, lavorarci non √® mai stato cos√¨ piacevole, i caricamenti sono molto pi√π brevi e le modifiche vengono fatte ormai in maniera quasi istantanea.Tutto sommato √® un prodotto di ottima fattura, assolutamente consigliata.', "I have a decent pc but the one thing I never upgraded was my ram, I have been using the same standerd crucial ram for years and was noticing my fps was very unstable, no matter if it was Battlefield 2042 I was playing or a less demanding game like ffxiv.As well as that frames issues I was also so faced with my system getting a lot of errors.I knew all my parts were newish so I couldn't be them and decided to get some ram because it was the only thing that was left that could be playing up, as soon as I booted up and put on that beautiful XMP my system was super smooth and games are always locked perfectly to the cap I use (144) this ram prices its fast and reliable.", 'Livraison rapide et conforme √† la commande.', 'Super comme toujours avec cette marque mon fils en est tr√®s content je recommande üëåüëå', Reviews: ['Todo bien, ok', "The G.Skill Trident RAM is a high-performance memory module that I have been using for a few years now and decided to add more to my system. This RAM is designed to provide blazing-fast speeds, exceptional stability, and unmatched reliability, making it an excellent choice for demanding applicationsOne of the key features of this RAM is its high frequency and low latency. With its exceptional speed, stability, and reliability, this RAM is sure to take your system to the next level. Whether you're a gamer, a content creator, or a professional, the G.Skill RAM is an investment that you won't regret.", 'Works well and compatible with my current memory. Lights up great', 'Came new in new packaging. Clock speed was preset perfect, and took right off with no tweaks.', 'One of the few ram sticks where xmp would work as intended on our x570 Taichi', "I used these for my new build with a ryzen 5 3600 and gigabyte x570 aorus elite motherboard. I kept having crashes that showed kernal power error event 41 and the sound would pop and crackle, when I was playing any intensive games. I tried a bunch of different stuff trying to find the problem and eventually turned the xmp profile off and found that I didn't have any crashes, turned xmp back on and the crashes came back. Found a review on newegg and someone had a similar issue and they underclocked em just below the stock xmp profile frequency  and it fixed the issue. I did the same and this fixed the issue for me too, I think mine are 3526mhz or 1763 ea stick. I tried upping the soc voltage and that didn't stop the crashes, but to be fair I've never really been big into overclocking and I didn't want to damage anything so I didn't go very much more than stock. I checked gigabytes website on supported ram sticks for my motherboard and cpu combo and they weren't listed (this is after I'd already found out I was having issues with them), I think eventually a new bios update with make them 100% compatible tho and honestly I don't mind running just under 3600mhz on my ram since its still better than 3200mhz. They look good and I like lights but i'd prolly gone with a different model that was listed as compatible with my mobo and cpu combo.TL;DR - Good ram, Nice lights, Check your motherboard companies cpu and ram compatibility info or you may have to do a little more work.", "Ok first off this is hynix die and it will reach 3600 but mine would crash so I turned mine down to 3533 and is stable at that frequency. I do wish it was stable at 3600 but not that big of a deal as it would be very minimal gains to reach that. I did have 3200 ram installed by the same company and was running 32 gigs. So my take on this, is if you have 3200 and is stable save your money and keep what ya have as I feel it not worth the extra 400 mhz to get the top speed. The only reason I did this was I have the AMD 12 core Ryzen and wanted to know if I could reach 4.5 ghz with my cpu.Update as I went into the bios I did a few tweaks to the settings and getting the ram stable at 3600 even in gaming and stress testing. I manually had to set the timing to 16 19 19 38. and voltage at 1.35 volts, hope this help others for some weird reason my asus motherboard wanted to auto to 16 18 18 38, and thats why in would crash as these timings are a bit too tight.  Update 2, As I've been working with this ram I have to say I really love it so well I bought another kit to add to my set up. It boots right up with the modded timing in the bios with no crashes with 32 gigs installed.", "I see others saying these kits struggle to get 3600Mhz and I am not sure what kinda of configuration they're trying to run, but mine is running perfectly fine at 3600Mhz. I bought these to replace Corsair RGB Pro's that were causing a lot of weird issues on my systems and from the looks of it, these did the trick. I do a lot of system building so I tend to buy a lot of the corsair kits because they're available locally at bestbuy, but I am not making that mistake again, I am steering clear of Corsair and will be using g.skill on my AMD builds like I've always done in the past. I still have hundreds of gigs of old school g.skill ddr3 ram that still work great.Yes these are Hynix and not Samsung memory, but that's okay, they're a still a good company and these kits are great. My only complaint, and while for this price it's not much of a complaint, but the white piece on the ram itself that the LED's shine through is a bit flimsy, but the kits I purchase by Corsair were same price and 400Mhz slower and did not OC very well and gave me nothing but headaches. Overall I would say they're worth the money and the software is easy to use.", 'Gained significant fps and it‚Äôs kinda weird but they made my cpu run a lot cooler', "Needed to up the voltage to 1.36 to make it 100% stable. Might be able to get away with 1.355, because it was like 99.999% stable at 1.35, maybe I just had a slightly bad stick. Not sure if that's a problem with the ram, my motherboard, or even that I was running four sticks. Other than that, they look great and meet their timings. I run 32gbs on an Asus B550 board and a Ryzen 5700G. I havent tried overlocking yet so I can't comment on that."]

Prisv√§rd uppgradering.', "Le prix est vraiment trop √©lev√© mais il me fallait atteindre 128Go , malheureusement j'en ai pas trouv√© d'autres moins ch√®res", "I boughjt this RAM for use with my new Ryzen 9 3900X. Here is my system:Motherboard: AsRock x570 Pro4CPU: Ryzen 9 3900XRAM: Corsair 2666 CL16 128 GB (4x32GB)NVMe: Silicon Power 2 TBGPU: Radeon Pro WX 2100Before buying this RAM, I tried various settings with RAM I took from another computer. My experiments confirmed that with all 4 slots filled, RAM works fine at 2666 @1.2V  I also tried 3200 CL14 RAM in all 4 slots. It did not work with XMP enabled, as predicted by the motherboard specs. But it worked fine at 2933 and 1.35V with all 4 slots filled, so you can use any DDR4 3000 MHz with it in all 4 slots. DDR4 3200 CL14 worked well with XMP enabled with 2 slots occupied. But for my project I absolutely needed 128 GB of RAM, so I bought the fastest available 4x32GB RAM (this one) for just $620 from Amazon (it is available at Corsair Web site at $610), and it works flawlessly with XMP enabled, at 1.2 V (and I don't want to overclock).With 3200 CL14 RAM my system scored 12650 under Geekbench 5 on Ubuntu 18.04 (and about 11850 with 2666 CL16 RAM).So if you absolutely need 128GB, get this one without doubts. If you need 64 GB, then get any 3000 RAM, and use it at 2933 and 1.35V (maybe, 3000 will also work). If you need you RAM to work at 3200 and higher, then you will be only able to use 2 slots (which means, up to 32 GB total because there are no 32GB DIMMs faster than this one on the market currently). Maybe 3200+ will work at higher DRAM voltage, but I don't want to try it.", 'Got this RAM installed a couple of weeks now and started to get Windows annoying messages of a faulty address. so i ran Windows Ram Diganostic test and it said i had an issue then i ran Memtest86 on it and found those error messages in the picture above. it did pass 24 tests out of 48. that is just 50% rate of success.---------------------------------------((Update)) i contacted Corsair and they sent me a DHL tracking number to send back the defected item and within 6 days they sent a fully functional RAM module all the way to be from their Factory in Taiwan with another RAM replacement. did not pay any shipping what so ever and i happy running my PC with this RAM. for such a customer support at Corsair i would give them 10/10 no question asked and i would recommend getting these if you want a solid RAM that is not huge and would be used under a big Fan such as the one from Noctua cooler, also anyone getting in RAM should always consider running a memTest once they get their RAM installed best to inspect each stick individually to narrow down the defected RAM module.  Then you contact the Manufacturing company if you are still under the warranty Period.', 'Fait tourner Hogwarts legacy, tout est dit!', "It worked. Had some trouble with the install but that was due to incorrect seating of the RAM. I had to push a bit harder until I heard a click. It almost looked like I might break the motherboard but it was necessary to seat the RAM correctly.I had to go into the bios and select an XMP profile to get the 3000 mhz RAM speed.Before you buy, you will have to check your motherboard's manufacturer website to see if that specific motherboard supports the RAM card. Otherwise it would probably only give you the base DDR4 speed of 2133 mhz.", 'These do what I ask of it.  I cannot complain. The price is great for what you get.']

I don't care about RGB, just performance, and so far this ram seems to be the best value out there (if you can live without RGB).The ram works with both Intel and AMD boards. It's low profile for cases with large air coolers or AIOs and It's Samsung b-die. Overall a great value at the current price of around $160 per kit.For more than 16gb 2 (or 4) kits must be ordered so that's approx $320 (at current) but to compare: a similar Dominator 3600mhz C16 32gb kit is about $450, so $130 more for RGB at a worse spec.My motherboard has 4 dimms but if it had 8 then it would be possible to purchase 4 kits and have 64 gb. Regardless, this ram should be purchased in pairs so either 1 kit, 2 kits or 4 kits and for me the sweet spot was 2 kits for the best price to performance.Caveats: motherboard must have good power regulation. I'm using an EVGA Dark X299 so I am not concerned about the 1.45V necessary for the XMP profile. This is fine as it is rated this way by Corsair. So long as the motherboard supports this voltage just set the XMP1 profile and all good. However, I don't see this ram as being able to overclock beyond 3600 mhz since it's already overclocked by Corsair at (what I think) is close to it's maximum (listed as only PC4-21300 in HWINfo). I personally don't care since for a stable x299 daily driver 3600mhz is where I wanted to be at with C16 timing or better. This ram is C14...so even better.So far so good, 100% stable but if issues arise I will update this review.", 'I run a Noctua NH-D15 and the LPX line from Corsair is the only "high performance" memory I could find that not only performs like I want, but also fits under the cooler. I\'ve purchased several of the LPX kits from Corsair over the years, and they never disappoint. Haven\'t tried overclocking it yet, but this kit runs at the advertised 3600Mhz C14 speed with no problem.I\'ve run this kit with two systems so far. First is an ASUS Crosshair VIII Hero X570 with a 3900X and the other is a Gigabyte AORUS Extreme X570 with a 3600XT. Both worked perfectly. The Gigabyte board required that I manually set the memory voltage when setting XMP in the BIOS but I believe that to be a board issue, not a memory issue. It\'s just worth noting that this memory does require 1.45V when running the XMP profile which isn\'t a big deal, just be sure it\'s set correctly in your BIOS.UPDATE 7 months later:After now having this kit run flawlessly with a Ryzen 3900X and now a Ryzen 3600XT I have ordered another pair. It seems AMD Ryzen Zen3 actually produces higher performance with 4 sticks of ram vs. only running 2. This is opposite what we have all experienced before, but this is no longer the case with the new 5000 series lineup of Ryzen processors. So, having such good results with the initial kit, I have ordered a second kit.So far I have yet to find another memory kit with this speed (3600MHz) and extreme low latency (C14). Almost everything else is C15 or higher. Love it!!', 'The other review about ram overclocking not working above 3600mhz is wrong. I have 4 systems with the cpu i9 10850K, I7 10700k, 5950x, and 5600x, in which they all excepted an overclock to 3866 at c14 or more precisely 14-14-14-30. It can push higher as well, but cas increases. initially 3866 runs at 14 15 15 36 on my Intel systems for try me memory with a 1.5v supplie but can be dumbed down to 1.4 as can the stock xmp @ 3600mhz from 1.45Update! On my 5600x w/3090 system I can 4x8 32gb @ 3800 c14  with extremely low tight timings. Latency is 51ns w/o errors w 51 read and 29.5 write', 'I got really lucky and got 2 sets at $109 each for my x299 platform with a i9 7980xe 18 core. With very little tuning i got it to 3800mhz 14-14-14-28 at 1.5v or 15-15-15-28 at 4000mhz. I do need a fan on them to run that kind of speed for a daily oc. But I have pushed them much farther, just not for daily.', 'I want more', "The sticker on the back of the RAM was exactly what (Samsung B Die Finder) it was supposed to be to actually be B die. Thaiphoon burner says it's Samsung 1 die and single rank ram. Sent mine back as the value just isn't there for $129.Update.I was a little harsh with the review just because it's not Samsung B Die, doesn't mean it's not good memory.  I bumped it a star.", "Wasn't sure these sticks were real with these specs.  Couldn't find them even on Corsair's own website.  But they arrived yesterday and are running at the noted speed and latency with zero issues once XMP was enabled. For reference I run an AMD 3700x on an MSI X570 Gaming Plus motherboard. Some may experience issues with other boards as is the nature of pc hardware. No problems here however.", 'Great speed noticed the difference from my 3200c16 set straight away.Havent tried pushing the overclock yet. But no issues running memtest with xmp active', 'The RAM specs is as advertised CL14-16-16-36 @1.45 and I gna definitely buy another 1 next month to sum up 32GB RAM to complete the set.Motherboard: Asus x570 Dark Hero with D.O.C.P (enable)Processor: AMD 5900x 12 core.Cooler: Noctua NH-D15s (Alot of RAM clearance for "Noctua NF-A14 PWM 140mm fan")Excellent product and speedy service. Thank you Amazon.']

Product: Crucial Ballistix RGB 3200 MHz DDR4 DRAM Desktop Gaming Memory Kit 16GB (8GBx2) CL16 BL2K8G32C16U4WL (White)
Reviews:
['Product came packaged well, works properly.', "The media could not be loaded.
                



\xa0Crucial really have struck diamond with these ballistix kits. Micron rev.e is amazingly good value when compared to offerings from Samsung and Hynix in the same price category, I know Ive got the RGB version but for ¬£10 less (at the time of writing) you can get the non-RGB version which perform identically. The similarly priced kits from the other brands usually use Samsund C die, like the Vengeance RGB Pro kit I owned previously, which have very, very little room for any overclock and I think it actually caused some OS degradation.I'm yet to overclock this kit because my CPU's IMC is pretty garbage, but after I upgrade that I'll definitely be giving it a shot. Currently running the kit at the XMP settings which is 3200MHz CL 16-18-18-36.I've seen people post results of getting this 3200mhz cl16 kit up to 3800 CL16, with slightly looser primaries and secondaries ofc, but it's still mind blowing that it can be done on these cheap kits. You'd need decent Samsung B die to get this level and the kits that use them cost considerably more money, which doesn't make sense to buy unless you're aiming for 4000MHz+, but at that point you're hitting diminishing return levels.The sticks are also much lower profile than my old kit which means they won't interfere with the big tower coolers like the NH-D15 and Dark Rock 4.The kits comes out the box with the rainbow wave RGB mode which doesn't stay synced for very long. Luckily this kit supports basically all the major motherboard RGB softwares, and it also has its own Ballistix MOD software that u can use to check dimm temperature, operating frequency and timings. There's also the section to control RGB and to give Crucial credit there are lots of different customisation options.Onto the *only* thing I don't like about this kit, and that's the way they've gone about the RGB. Unlike my Corsair kit, these dimms won't keep my RGB settings after they lose power, ie after I shut down my PC. They will default to the rainbow mode until I launch the software manually. And if you set the software to boot with windows it asks for admin permissions EVERY. SINGLE. TIME. and it gets annoying, and even with the app enabled to start up it will only use the colour/mode you set; you have to change the brightness manually every time if you don't want your LEDs burning at max brightness. With my Corsair kit I could set the colour/mode/brightness I wanted and then disable iCue software from ever launching, and those sticks would remember the last setting no matter how many times I turned the PC off and on. I'm guessing Corsair were smart enough to include some type of memory chip on the RAMs PCB to remember the RGB settings without having to run any bloatware. Disappointed to see Crucial could not follow suitOther than that minor gripe, these sticks look and run great", "I have no complaints about the RAM itself. They have excellent quality Micron chips running @ 3200mhz with no issues. The heat spreaders are compact, well designed and I have steady temps around 29c. Great! My only complaint is the RGB. You pay an extra premium for those and it should be expected that they operate well. They are indeed bright but the color transitions are choppy as hell. They seem to only be on or off with no color blending if you are using the rainbow or other color gradient effects. Also they don't really follow a color wheel using the rainbow setting so it will transition from pure Red straight into pure Blue with no pleasant gradient through Purple. Sometimes it's Green straight into Red, skipping  what would naturally happen, which is Yellow to Orange THEN to Red. It's just Green then (BAM!) Red to start the cycle again. Part of the issue might be the software but I've used both Crucial's software and the native MB software and it's the same Choppy on/off color transitions with no smooth gradients. I may try OpenRGB next and if it doesn't work it's not the end of the world, but I expected a little better for the premium I paid for the aesthetics.", 'The pest I‚Äôve used hands down!! They have lasted me so far for 3 years! And they‚Äôre still running really fast and durable! Not to mention the RGB is great!', 'premetto che queste ram le ho comprate a 60‚Ç¨ in offerta, che dire, sono veramente prestanti e belle esteticamente, unico difetto purtroppo √® che non riesco a gestire gli rgb tramite aura sync, leggendo in vari forum ho visto che non sono l unico ad avere questo problema..CONCLUSIONI: se non avete esigenza di controllare gli rgb e magari trovate un banco di ram in offerta direi che √® un buon acquisto', "Want low profile RAM? Want it in RGB? Here you go. This memory is barely taller than the Corsair LPX and the difference isnt even noticeable. So if you have something like a Noctua NH-D15 and want some glow this is your memory. The colors fluctuate between solid colors stock setting instead of a rainbow effect. You'll need crucial software to change this effectUnfortunately this RAM didn't play well with my wife's Ryzen 3600 and X570 board. For one it wouldn't boot with both sticks and couldn't hold an XMP overclock. I tested them on my 8700K build they worked as advertised. Unfortunately I already have good Samsung B-die memory for that build while these Crucial sticks were for my wife's Ryzen build. So I had to return them. Were I looking for low profile RGB memory at an affordable price I would snatch em again up in a heartbeat", 'I have to use MSI‚Äôs mystic light software to control the lights as the MOD software that comes with these doesn‚Äôt save your RGB settings, so whenever your PC goes to sleep or powers off they return to the original light pattern.Not a big issue but something to note.They look really nice in white and the RGB is really pretty and bright', 'I recently purchased ballistics tactical tracers and I was so disappointed as the rgb was super dim and made a high pitched noise when on. I didn‚Äôt realise that these were cheaper and better so I got these instead and returned the old ones. I really didn‚Äôt want to get Corsair memory as they never run at the speed stated on the box so I really wanted to get these. I installed them and was instantly blown away by how bright they were and vibrant. Out of the box they worked with XMP 3200mhz but after some tweaking and looking at reviews I got them at 3600mhz stable and I‚Äôm super happy with them the pictures don‚Äôt show the rgb it‚Äôs justice but they look amazing in person. I‚Äôll be recommending these to anyone looking for rgb fast ram.', 'Memoria RAM DDR4 3200 MHz montadas en una placa Aorus B450 PRO, el funcionamiento es correcto como pongo en las fotos, las velocidades las que marca el fabricante, la √∫nica pega es el RGB su software no me gusto es bastante pesado y no se iniciaba solo con Windows 10, gigabyte saco una actualizaci√≥n que las hizo compatibles con el RGB fusi√≥n 2.0 y as√≠ las tengo ahora, y el resultado es mejor ya que se sincroniza con los colores de la placa, eso si cuando arranca el software RGB fusi√≥n 2.0 en Windows as√≠ que tarda un poco no es instant√°neo', 'The installation was easy just popping out the old ram and putting these ones in 5/5The setting up was had some problems enabling xmp was fine, but the ram wasn‚Äôt showing up on my RGB fusion, so I downloaded the mod software, some of the worse RGB software I‚Äôve used, showed a error message opening my pc, so I needed to update my bios, and then it showed up. 4/5It could of just been a old bios update issue.The stability is good I just enabled xmp and I‚Äôve had no boot issues since, unlike my old Corsair LPX had issues. 5/5']

Reviews: ["A year ago I bought 2x16Gb Corsair RAM to upgrade my iMac. Installatie is een fluitje van een cent. Het geheugen wordt onmiddellijk herkend na opstart.', 'Ottimo rapporto qualit√† prezzo', 'Lo adquir√≠ para aumentar la RAM al iMac 27‚Äù del 2017.Es compatible y no he tenido ning√∫n problema con la RAM desde entonces.Sin embargo, tiene un precio muy elevado para las pocas prestaciones que tiene.', 'I have a mid-2017 iMac 27 inch Retina with the 3.4 GHz Quad-Core Intel Core i5. I just upgraded the memory by replacing the OEM 8gb (2x4gb) with 32gb of OWC RAM (4x8gb).  Some people have reported problems following the upgrade - e.g. not being able to reboot, etc.  Just one data point, but I didn\'t have any problems at all. Shut down the computer, pulled out the OEM cards, plugged in the four new OWC cards, and turned the power back on.  Will update later if the memory fails in the future - a problem others reported. Fingers crossed, but so far, the upgrade was simple and fast. NOTE that the computer was generally a little "slow" immediately following the reboot (when starting an application, for example), but that apparently is normal as various information is re-initialized. After a few minutes, performance was back to normal, and much better with several apps open because of the additional memory.IMPORTANT: Note that according to Apple, the 3.4 ghz processor maxes out at 32gb total. It\'s a little hard to find that fact online, but it is a limitation specifically for the 3.4 ghz processor. The 3.5 ghz and above can supposedly accommodate 64gb.', 'The reasons for the 4 stars is that the laptop has a crappy processor and 1 of the 2 ram slots were damaged, enforcing to get this 32g ram one. It do detect the full 32 and it works as expected. This is a personal feeling and it has nothing to do with the memory itself since the laptop cannot use his full power anyway.', "j'ai augment√© la RAM de mon IMAC 2017.Installation tr√®s simple et cela fonctionne sans probl√®me .Produit √† recommander en suivant bien s√ªr les correspondances ordinateur-m√©moire.", 'Speeding up my lenovo to the max.
