I have no plans to overclock it, so cannot say anything about it.The heat spreaders are fairly tall, but easily fit under Noctua NH-D15's cutout. Check your cooler size, as normal.", 'Eventuell in dieser Bewertung genannte Markennamen sind Eigentum ihrer jeweiligen Hersteller/Inhaber in Deutschland und/oder anderen L√§ndern.Vorwort:Ich habe mir erst hier auf Amazon die GSkill  2666er RAM\'s gekauft. Diese haben aber inYoutube Videos so seltsame Artefakte und gr√ºne Streifen produziert. Im Hardwarehilfe Forum wurde mir gesagt, dass sie gerne mal Fehler h√§tten. Die R√ºcksendung sowie Erstattung bei Amazon haben reibungslos funktioniert, Vielen Dank Amazon:-)So nun zur Review:Ich  habe mir die Kinston Fury Renegade 3200er RAM\'s zwei Mal  aus oben genannten Gr√ºnden gekauft.Bestellt wurden sie am 3.05, geliefert am 05.05.Packungsinhalt ist wie folgt:- 2x8 GB Kingston Fury Renegade 3200er Riegel- 1x ein kleines Garantie- und Installationsbl√§ttchen- 1x ein Kingston Fury Sticker zum Aufkleben auf\'s Geh√§useDie Ram Riegel machen aufgrund des Heatspreaders ordentlich was her.Sie haben zwer kein RGB, aber davon habe ich genug im Rechner.Zusatz 1: Ich wei√ü nicht, was die Sternekategorie "Genauigkeit" hei√üt. Falls damit gemeint ist, dass sie genau ins System passen, ist die volle Sterneanzahl erreicht.Zusatz 2:  Ich bewerte in der Sternekategorie "Qualit√§t/Haltbarkeit" NUR die Qualit√§t, zur Haltbarkeit kann ich nichts sagen, da ich die Riegel erst im System verbaut habe.Zusatz 3: Bei diesen RAM\'s handelt es sich um Kits, d.h. es sind 2 8 GB Riegel in einer Packung. Da ich aber schon eine Riegel ins System gesetzt habe, ist auf den Fotos nur einer zu sehen.Anmerkung: Die Dino\'s auf dem Bild sind nicht Teil des Lieferinhalts, ich wollte den beigelegten Sticker zeigen, aber der klebt schon am Geh√§use. :-)Ich hoffe, dass die Review hilfreich war:-)', 'It looks fantastic on my Aorus Master inside that Silent Base 802! Reviews: ['Foi instalar e partir para o abra√ßo!', 'ÂãïÁîªÁ∑®ÈõÜ„ÇÑDTM‰ΩúÊ•≠„ÅÆÂäπÁéá„Ç¢„ÉÉ„Éó„Åß32GB„Å´„Åó„Åü„Åè„ÄÅË©ï‰æ°„ÅÆËâØ„ÅÑ„Åì„Å°„Çâ„ÇíË≥ºÂÖ•‰ªä„ÅÆÊâÄ‰∏çÂÖ∑Âêà„ÇÇ„Å™„ÅèÊïÖÈöú„ÇÇ„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„Å™„ÅÑ„ÅÆ„ÅßÊ∫ÄË∂≥„Åó„Å¶„ÅÑ„Åæ„Åô', 'Buon rapporto qualit√† prezzo', 'Ram working is very nice for work and gaming purpose', 'It is a good upgrade for my gaming computer', 'As with all memory, all ways check your motherboard/PC specs to make sure the memory specs are compatible, and your bios/UEFI is up to date.That being said like most sticks of ram it works or it doesn‚Äôt, just make sure they are well seated, and depending on the motherboard you may have to install one and reboot then power down and install the other.I have no issues with this ram, and it works great!I up graded my 2021 Dell Aurora 10,AMD Ryzen 9 5950X (16-Core, 72MB Total Cache, Max Boost Clock of 4.9GHz)32gb Hyper Fury 3200Mhz DDR4 Dual Channel32gb Corsair Ballistic 3200mhz DDR4 Dual ChannelNVIDIA GeForce RTX 3080 10GB GDDR6X', "I have this 32GB memory set working flawlessly on an Asus B460i ITX Motherboard; In the UEFI/BIOS, the ram speed is 2133 by default and I was able to get both sticks running at the rated speeds of 2666 Mhz by enabling it in a drop down menu. I didn't have any issue on initial POST and the memory is paired with an i5 10400f processor.The memory are low profile with a predominately black heat shielding; I chose this non-RGB version as my CPU cooler does cover the memory slots and needed the height clearance. Very easy to install and clicks in when seated in the memory slots securely.", 'Installed easily, easy overclocking and consistently high performance .The ram has surprised me with its stability. A solid investment for highly reliable ram.', "I recently bought an alienware PC (ryzen) and wanted to upgrade the RAM without paying for Dell's overpriced memory. Once installed, the computer recognized the new modules without any issues. The timinigs of the ram is slightly different from the one that came with the computer, even though they are both made by Kingston and have the same clock frequency. I've had no problems with the modules so far, so definetly I would recommend them for alienware RAM upgrades, at least the 2666 MHz sticks.", "They look great, the heat spreaders are nice. The color is fantastic. Every PC builder loves the little stickers the manufacturers send with their product :D, and Kingston sends one as well. Installed in my system, and without having to use any XMP profiles, system detected the full 32GB, running at the expected 2666MHz speed. Highly satisfied, and it seems stable in my system. For the price, and value you really can't go wrong with Hyper X. I will also say the CAS latency at 16 is really good too."]

Reviews: ['Well, product is good but you need to really check before buying this if your specific laptop works smoothly or not with this frequency and overall specifications.I had issues, actually this was accumulation of two different problems.1. Laptop refused to boot up after popping in two new sticks.2. 2nd slot stick was not going in correctly, when I tried older memory stick it went in smoothly. Had to try multiple times before 2nd slot stick stuck inside. Which was unusual, this is not supposed to happen. Fyi, this is not problem with stick but the laptop manufacturing, second slot locking pins were just tad bit smaller, HK hynix (old stick) was fitting in perfectly but this one is just fractionally bigger, and I mean real small fraction.My laptop is acer 7 aspire 715-51G 12th gen.And booting issues was solved after I removed CMOS battery pin (yes, have to remove the pin as battery is enclosed with the pin itself using black taping material. Kept pin removed for about 2 min before inserting back.Still need to do lot of checking as when on battery power laptop was not turning on, above solution is when I started using wall plug. Will try battery boot in couple of days, let the system adjust to the change first. lol sounds funny considering this is machine and not human.Try to get your hands on KC version of these sticks rather than KVR, KC ones are factory tested to work on specific models and KV ones are more general purpose.Where to check compatibility? Go on kingston website, look up your laptop model exactly. Similar thing can be done for crucial.', "Yeah and the overall performance of my laptop's memory usage has been immensly increased. Though I feel there's some overheating in the portion where I installed the RAM, I am not sure if it's actually because of it.", 'Good product.', "Purchased two Kingston 16GB DDR4 3200Mhz Non ECC Laptop Memory CL 22,RAM SODIMM (KVR32S22D8/16), Green; compatible with Asus TUF F15 as per the Kingston website. The power is being drained out after the RAM upgrade, so I'm unsure if it's due to the RAM or if any settings would have to be updated in Armoury Crate. Research more if you're upgrading your Asus TUF laptop. The RAM is reliable and works as expected.", "Arrived quickly, packed with M2 SSD disk in standard Amazon cardboard envelope, decent packing. Works OK, inside NUC 12 Pro, without any trouble on a first boot. Been running it for few days. Did not run any benchmarks, did not run any games, and don't know how it will work long term. Kingston memories are good, so I don't expect issues.", 'Ram is good.Bought two3200mhz  ddr4 modules of 16 gb each for laptop.Cpu-z software is showing  that ram is outputting full 3200mhz, means ram is giving what it promised.Moreover, its a dual rank ram, which  exactly a gimmick or reality i dont know but as per many reviews dual rank rank is better than single rank ram.Same 16gb ddr4 dual rank ram for laptop of hynix is much cheaper in price, with approx difference of Rs1000 and that is also dual rank ram.So if you find hynix ram from a trusted seller on amazon, then i advice you to go for hynix ram.Crucial ram of 3200mhz16gb laptop ddr4,is a single rank ram but they advertize it as dual rank ram, so i didnt buy that.Any way crucial is also a good option.In a nut shell,this kingston ram is working fine, but price is on a higher side.', "I ordered 16 GB 3200Mhz ddr4 SODIMM... its dual rank x8 bus which is better than x16... its good legit ram... though Crucial ram is cheaper but there is a 50-50 percent chance that you'll get dual rank... so I avoided that... plus Kingston ram comes with a lifetime warranty.", 'I bought this memory KVR32S22D8/16 because it was listed on the Compatability List for my new Asus PN51 mini pc.Other memory not on the list did not work. I have never seen such a worst condition of the packaging. It looked like thousand year old product. I mean seriously there is a thing called ‚Äúpresentation ‚Äú. Work on that part. About the Ram. Reviews: ['Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 3200MHz ist ein gro√üartiger RAM f√ºr Gaming und anspruchsvolle Anwendungen. Die Installation war einfach und die Leistung ist beeindruckend. Der RAM ist stabil und zuverl√§ssig und hat eine schnelle Daten√ºbertragungsrate. Die Corsair Vengeance LPX Serie ist bekannt f√ºr ihre hohe Qualit√§t und Leistung und dieser RAM ist keine Ausnahme. Wenn Sie auf der Suche nach einem zuverl√§ssigen und leistungsstarken RAM-Modul sind, dann ist der Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 3200MHz eine gro√üartige Wahl', '√ßa fait 4 ans sans soucis', "Even though my PC is a closed box, solid sides, I still wanted a spalsh of my signature colour inside the white case with predominantly black components!  Don't be put off by some of the pictures you see of this that make it look like a flat, dull red.  These sticks of RAM are like a sparkly candy-apple red, as shown in some photos of it installed.Other than that, er, yeah, it's RAM.  A few things for you to consider thought when buying RAM:1. What will your CPU actually support?  A core i7 9700 (like I have) will only take advantage of 2666MHz.  You can use faster RAM like this, but the gains for Intel are marginal.2. Faster RAM doesn't necessarily mean better.  Aside from capacity, RAM also comes with a couple of other key numbers.  Speed (3200MHz in this case) and latency (C16 in this case).  You need to consider both, and there is a formula for it (assuming dual channel here):latency/speed*2000 = 16/3200*2000 = 10nanosecondsIf you do the maths, you'll see that 15/3000*2000 also equals 10 nanoseconds.  So, you'll often find that faster ram has slightly worse latency, which broadly balances out.  So why buy faster if slower can ultimately perform the same on paper?  More bandwidth - simple as that.  For a given latency, yes, more MHz is better, and you are always better off getting as much bandwidth as you can afford, but, you'll find that high speed and low latency starts to get very expensive very quickly and for marginal gains (read, bragging rights).It also depends on what you are using your PC for as to what to get.  For gaming, you aren't going to get much benefit from super-fast RAM and using more than 16GB of it.  There's always a performance/benefit curve with PCs and components, and the best PCs are those that use components in good balance.", 'Una memoria RAM con muy buena relaci√≥n calidad precio, las compr√© para ampliar mi PC a 32 gigas y sin problemas, f√°cil instalaci√≥n muy recomendables.', 'Hallo zusammen,hatte diesen Speicher auf einem ASUS Crosshair VI hero im Einsatz, dazu ne M2-SSD etc.Verbaut war weiterhin ein R3-1200 (Standardtakt). Bis auf das Board bei Amazon erworben.Lief zun√§chst problemlos mit 3200/16-18-18 etc. via D.O.C.P.Via Amazon hatte ich inzwischen noch ein weiteres Paar RAMs (dieselben, nur in schwarz) bestellt, eine gr√∂√üereM2-NVMe, zzgl. Apdaterkarte. Auch das lief (erstmal) sauber.Dann gings aber los.Allerlei wirklich seltsame Fehler, blue screens unter Last, ohne Last, Fehler beim Kopieren, Checksum errors und weiteres mehr, das volle Programm eben. X-mal Windows neu installiert, Systemdateien fehlten, Reparatur viaDISM bzw. SFC scheiterten quasi immer, zudem trat die Fehler nach kurzer Zeit erneut auf. Das roch erstmal nach SSD:Mainboard zeigte je nach Mondphase mal Speicherfehler an, mal CPU defekt, mal Mainboard error, so wie es ebenLust hatte. Arbeiten war damit absolut nicht mehr m√∂glich. Alles durchgetestet, RAMs zeigten KEINE Fehler an.Nochmal getestet, nat√ºrlich alle Riegel auch einzeln. Die nachgeorderten Riegel retourniert, hatte erst die im Verdacht, ebenso die M2-SSD und die Apapterkarte (da fehlte eh ne Schraube, M2 konnte daher nicht befestigt werden und ein Kabelbinder kann da nicht die Dauerl√∂sung sein).Problem war immer noch da, also waren es nicht die neuen Riegel und auch nicht die SSD gewesen.Netzteil konnte ich ausschliessen, ein Quertest mit einem nagelneuen (danke Nachbar!) ergab dasselbe Fehlerbild.Inzwischen kamen doch mehrheitlich RAM-Fehler raus, das war dann schon recht eindeutig, aber eben nicht absolut sicher. Aufgrund extrem hohen Temindrucks brauchte ich dringend Ersatz, daher woanders per Express geordert.Da ich nicht sicher wusste wo denn nun eigentlich der Fehler lag habe ich das komplette Paket (Mainboard/CPU/RAM) bestellt (war nicht eben billig, aber in diesem Fall absolut notwendig).Erstmal nur die RAMs (jetzt Patriot Viper 4, 3733, 2St 2x8G=32G) getauscht und siehe da: Seither ist Ruhe.Sowohl noch mit dem 3-1200, als auch mit nem Ryzen 7, keine Probleme mehr.Es war also eindeutig der Speicher.All der √Ñrger hat ne Unmenge Zeit und Nerven gekostet (ein-/ausbauen, neu installieren, testen, Kopp auf Tischplatte hauen etc pp. und all das nicht nur einmal).Habe quasi alles retourniert (CPU, die RAMs und die SSD), was blieb mir denn sonst auch √ºber?Ausdr√ºcklich loben m√∂chte ich Amazon, all der Krams wurde sehr kulant und zu meiner absoluten Zufriedenheitabgewickelt. H√§tte ich vorher gewusst wo das Problem lag w√§re zumindest eine R√ºcksendung teilweise nicht n√∂tig gewesen. Aber h√§tte, w√§re, wenn ...M√∂chte den RAM aber nicht verteufeln, das kann leider mal vorkommen. War wohl eindeutig ein MontagsproduktAnsonsten wirkt er durchaus wertig, schaut auch gut aus (wobei das v√∂llig zweitrangig ist, muss zuverl√§ssig laufen).Insofern gebe ich mal drei Sterne, aufgrund des √Ñrgers w√§re es jedoch nur einer, Amazon bekommt sechs!', 'lo mejor el precio', 'Comprate in sostituzione delle vecchie hyperx da 2400 che cominciavano a dare riavvii continui.Le ho montate in dual channel su una B350M della MSI (mortar arctic). Con il nuovo bios (novembre 2018) riconosce il profilo XMP 2.0 che √® proprio il 3200. Certo, non parliamo di memorie CL14 ad alte prestazioni, ma il ryzen in ogni caso sfrutta meglio di intel l\'alta frequenza e questo √® evidente in molti giochi. Per esempio ho portato il limite massimo di fps oltre la stabilit√† dei 200 fps senza effetto "sali-scendi" (prima invece era altalenante tra 110 e 200).Ho notato, inoltre, una notevole riduzione di effetto stuttering.Per quanto riguarda la percentuale minima di fps (1% min low fps) purtroppo rimane come con le 2400. In effetti, se la scheda video non regge √® inutile appellarsi a delle 3200mhz sperando di risolvere il problema. Se la GPU non ce la fa, non ce la fa. Sicuramente se con le 2400 ottenete 55fps, con le 3200 vi avvicinate a 59-60 (piacevole all\'occhio) ma non supererete mai i 60.Consigliate su build con ryzen, prezzo: 145 a dicembre 2018. Se oltrepassate i 160, puntate su gskill.', '¬°LEER OPINI√ìN ENTERA ANTES DE COMPRAR!Le pongo 1 estrella porque yo ya ten√≠a 2 modulos de 8GB a 3200GHz. He querido comprar otros 2 modulos para que sean 4 de la misma empresa,velocidad, capacidad y caracter√≠sticas.Cuando he querido realizar Overclock en mi PC para poner las RAM a 3200GHz (activar XMP) al parecer al ordenador no le gustaba y se reiniciaba haciendo que la configuraci√≥n realizada en la BIOS se eliminar√°.¬øQue sucede? Los primeros modulos los compre hace 3 a√±os, en la pegatina de cada modulo (NO APARECE NI EN LA CAJA NI EN LA WEB) indica la versi√≥n de ese modelo. Las RAM que ten√≠a eran verson 4.3, las adquiridas nuevas eran 4.5 y por ser de diferentes versiones no funcionan...Mi soluci√≥n fue cambiar las RAM con otro ordenador que tenia en casa los cuales justamente eran la misma version que las primeras. Mi opini√≥n final es que si vais a adquirir estas RAM, comprar 4 modulos directamente para as√≠ en un futuro cuando querrais ampliar la memoria RAM, no os pase como a mi.Espero haber ayudado y que a nadie le suceda lo mismo ya que en mi caso he tenido otro ordenador en casa, si no fuera asi, tendria que haber devuelto los modulos o haberme comprado otros 2 modulos para tener 4 de la misma version.(A√±adir que parecia que los modulos nuevos no funcionaban muy bien en mi PC, pero si en el ordenador secundario. Y no es cosa de mi PC ya que tengo los 32GB a 3200MHz.)', 'Esta memoria vendida como premium es dual-sided; no funciona a la m√°xima velocidad con el controlador de memoria de mi Ryzen 5 3600XT. Arranca, pero cada x horas se corrompe algo lo cual es peligros√≠simo, y no pasa pruebas de memoria de Memtest86+. Tras contactar con el soporte de Corsair tuve que devolverla y buscarme una PC3200 single-sided.', 'Premessa:l\'acquisto di questi tre elementi √© stato dettato esclusivamente da motivi professionali.In breve, questi tre elementi combinati insieme forniscono una potenza elaborativa degna di nota e certamente al pari di un Intel i7 di sesta o settima generazione.Dichiaro qui il codice esatto dei banchi ram compatibili con la mother-board prelevati direttamente dal sito MSI, tenendo ben presente che la compatibilit√† non va oltre i 2.99mhz - anche aggiornando il bios.- codice ram compatibile: CMK16GX4M2B3200C16R -Ovviamente quando parlo di compatibilit√† intendo "lavorativa" per ore e giorni di seguito; non di certo un sermplice agganciamento "oh funziona!" e corri a scrivere una recensione menzoniera.A malincuore ho dovuto rendere tutti e tre gli elementi perch√© ASSOLUTAMENTE INCOMPATIBILI CON WINDOWS 7.Quindi: se usate Windows 8.1 o superiore gli elementi vanno bene cosi come sono, altrimenti il RYZEN-7 non √© per nulla indicato per Windows 7.']

Product: Crucial 4GB DDR3L 1600MHz SODIMM Memory for Mac Module (CT4G3S160BM)
Reviews:
['der Macbook pro l√§uft besser', 'Originally, I didn't think my RAM could be upgraded, I have a 15" mid-2012 MacBook Pro with 4GB. I read some of the reviews from others who have this model and even though the Apple website says it only holds 8GB, apparently people have been successful with 2 8GB sticks. I don't use my laptop for gaming, but I use fairly large programs to build websites, and just a lot of general multitasking, so I opted for getting 2 sticks of 4GB (so 8GB total).It was easy to install, I watched a YouTube video for my specific model. I did have to purchase a Phillips head #00 screwdriver from the hardware store, it was $5. Make sure you put the screws into a little bowl or something because the top right 3 are longer but the others are the smallest screws I have ever seen.When I first turned on my computer again, only one RAM stick was reading, the other said "empty". I switched them out again, putting the top stick on the bottom and the one I had on the bottom, I put on the top just to make sure it wasn't the RAM itself. It wasn't, I was an idiot and didn't have it in right I guess. Second time booting up, I went to About this Mac and Memory, it was reading correctly at 8GB total.The first thing I noticed was that when I switched user accounts, it loaded right away, as before it would take a good minute or more to switch over to the other user's log in screen. Also, my iMessages app would take ages to start and load messages, it worked almost instantly. My MacBook is running really fast as compared to before, so I am very happy with this purchase! I can't speak to using a total of 16GB of RAM because I didn't install that, BUT from other reviews I definitely think that it's fine with this particular model. Here I was looking at buying a new MacBook Pro, I just saved myself literally $1000 lol! This brought some new life back into my computer, so if you're looking for speed and loaded apps/multitasking it's totally worth it, I definitely think I have myself a couple more years on this bad boy.', 'This kit worked great with my Mid-2012 MacBook Pro 15''.To start off, I'm not a gamer. I don't do heavy computing and I'm not a big computer nerd. I use my computer for everyday things - surfing the internet, writing, using my calendar, communicating with friends, Excel/Word/Powerpoint, music & sampling, along with some designing (with Photoshop & Illustrator).Before I bought this, my computer was abnormally slow even though only half of my hard drive was full (it was slow to wake up, it took a while for apps to load, and there was always a lag when I switched apps). As soon as I switched my memory from 4GB to 8GB, it made a tremendous difference. All my apps run fast, I never have to reboot my computer (although I still do periodically) and everything feels like when I first got my MacBook.If you're on the fence of buying this, stop. Do your research and figure out if you really need this, otherwise you'll just waste your time, money, and energy. Use the Utilities found on your computer and specifically, "Activity Monitor" to determine how much memory your computer is using. I was pushing 3.99GB when I had 4GB available - that was problem #1. Oh, and if your computer is old, changing your memory is pointless. Just get a new computer.If you're looking to make your computer start faster, the problem isn't your memory (most likely). The problem is your hard drive - so you need to get a faster and bigger hard drive if your computer is too slow to boot up.And lastly, switching memory isn't the magic cure to making your computer run incredibly fast. You still need to take care of your computer - that means, periodic cleaning of your files, cache, and junk. Turning it on and off every now and then, and making sure you back up your files.You really only need to make a memory switch if 1) your apps are slow to load and it takes a while for you to switch from a program like Microsoft Word to Chrome. 2) When you wake your computer, it takes a solid 20-30 seconds before you can do anything. 3) Your Activity Monitor shows that you're pushing the limits for your memory.If you meet all of those qualifications, then get this! If not, figure out what you need by doing a Google search.', 'I upgraded my Mac Book Pro (mid 2012) from 4gm to 8 gb ram‚Ä¶..now enjoying the excellent speed. Great purchase.', 'My early 2011 Macbook Pro was slowing down to a crawl and I was beginning to see the spinning rainbow more and more often. Simply trying to open iPhoto took several minutes to load. I had looked into increasing my ram, as I still had the stock 2gb and amazon had the cheapest prices I could find. I tend to have several tabs open on Google Chrome while having music playing in the background and some other small tasks, so I thought 8gb would be enough, rather than shelling out $50+ more for the 16gb. Making the swap was easy and there are plenty of YouTube videos available if you need some help. It's as simple as unscrewing the bottom, making the swap, screwing it back on, and powering on your computer and letting the machine do the rest. Make sure not to lose any of the small screws while doing this. Ultimately I'm happy with my purchase but I wish I had spent the extra money for the 16gb. Make sure to open up Activity Monitor and see what your usage is before ordering. No complaints and my graphics even increased from 300mb to 512. I read that you don't need "for Mac" branded ram and regular DDR3 1600 will work but I decided not to risk it, and this version was even cheaper than the regular ones.P.S. If you really want to see your computer running like brand new, I would recommend installing an SSD drive. I went with the Samsung 850 EVO and my boot up time has decreased from a few minutes to a few seconds. (20<) Even my power consumption has decreased, allowing my battery to last a while longer and I don't feel the computer overheating anymore.While not the cheapest, these improvements are great investments and more affordable than shelling out for a newer computer.', 'I have had my Apple Macbook Pro (early 2011) now with basically no problems at all. The only thing I started realizing was the speed of everything. It took a long time to open any window. I started looking into upgrading memory and was told by apple to check out Crucial Memory. On their website they have a computer scanner that will quickly scan  your system to let you know what size you need and the maximum amount you can add. I located it and soon realized it was cheaper on Amazon's website with free shipping. I would recommend doing this. Crucial Still will back up their products even if you buy it from a third party company. The serial numbers however didn't match up which first had me concerned. I spoke to someone at Crucial and they advised the numbers may be different due to it not coming directly from the manufacture. So don't be fooled by the numbers.Installation was an absolute breeze. Quickly was able to unscrew all the little screws and pop out the old memory cards. Make sure you install the new ones the exact was the old memory comes out. Within 30 seconds it was installed.Now for the moment of truth. I checked the system under "about this Mac" and it now shows I have 8GB instead of 4GB. The results are absolutely amazing. I no longer have to wait for different programs to open. I also no longer get the little spinning wheel from time to time. It was a great buy and I would highly recommend it to anyone with a apple computer. Even if your speed seems okay, spend the money and upgrade! You won't be upset! Any questions please feel free to ask me. I can help you to the best of my ability.', "Normally, I'd write very in-depth reviews; however, in this instance, there isn't a need. The RAM pictured on the product page is what you receive, in a well-protected factory-sealed blisterpak. As long as you know what RAM you need (you can go to Crucial's website and use their Memory Advisor to see what chip your particular laptop needs and how much RAM your machine can handle -- in my case a DDR3-1600, for my son's Asus laptop), this is quite simply a five-star product that will breathe new life into your machine. The chip installed in seconds. My son's machine recognized it without issue. As expected, the upgrade allowed my son to do more multi-tasking. He's happier with his laptop; and, if he's happy, so am I. In my experience, if you go Crucial, you can't go wrong and I have no problem recommending this purchase.Of note, I worked, professionally, and continue to work, on the side, in the computer-repair business for 15+ years. While RAM upgrades are usually the least expensive and easiest of all the upgrades you can make to your machine, always ensure you know what you are doing before opening any machine. If you never replaced a RAM chip before... research, research, and research some more. If you don't know what you're doing -- RAM replacement is fairly simple and straightforward, but, if done wrong, can fry a motherboard (I learned that from experience many, many years ago) -- take your machine to someone who knows what they are doing. While I doubt I'll have a need to do so, given my extensive positive history with Crucial chips, if I have a need to change my review, for better or worse, I'll do so ASAP. Until then, regards.", 'These Crucial 8gig sticks (2 x 4gig)\xa0
Crucial 8GB Kit (4GBx2) DDR3/DDR3L 1600 MT/s (PC3-12800) CL11 204-Pin SODIMM Memory for Mac CT2K4G3S160BM / CT2C4G3S160BM
\xa0worked perfect in my in my ASUS CHROMEBOX-M004U Desktop PC Celeron 2955U (1.4GHz) 2GB DDR3 16GB SSD HDD model CN60.  They replaced the one slot 2gig ram factory installed stick (of course, now using both ram slots), even though the Chromebox specs says 4gig limit.  Lol, Asus should update their Chromebox specs cause they'd probably sell more Chromeboxes.  And yes, I know that if I'm only running ChromeOS that 2gig ram and 16 gig SSD works fine.I also threw in a "MyDigitalSSD SC2 Super Cache 2 42mm SATA III 6G M.2 NGFF M2 SSD Solid State Drive (128GB)"\xa0
MyDigitalSSD SC2 Super Cache 2 42mm SATA III 6G M.2 NGFF M2 2242 SSD Solid State Drive (128GB)
\xa0as per directions found on web by [...].I recommend first coning your USB stick with the ChromeOS (backup/recovery) image before you pull your box open to instal new ram, unless you have another pc within arm's reach.Thanks to Roger Stringer, my little chromebox is smoking hot!  No more dead tabs! Streaming netflix's without any stalls or hiccups.I will probably setup the dual boot to Linux next week when i have more "free time". LOL.I will also upgrade my two other chromeboxes soon.', "This brand that designed this ram in awesome! It can be a bit costly but the ram has great performance, great speed and the ability to process multiple things within a app or over several apps is great.  I've compared this brand 8gb to another  brand of 16 gb and  even at a smaller gb this brand out performed the 16gb. recommend this for those who use light to moderate weight software and app. If you use heavy apps then go for the 16gb of this brand. A key thing I look for to determine if i need to upgrade ram is when i am using my laptop (with proper ventilation) and it is showing a pattern running hot within certain software causing the software and the laptop to lag, move slow and/or freeze. A time here and there is no big thing but when this becomes the norm and the frequency of the laptop running hot while in the software has increased then it is time to upgrade ram. Since upgrading my ram to this brand and gb my laptop has not ran hot. I use this ram on my mid 2012 MacBook pro for light to moderate weighed software and basic every day use.", "With the end of Windows XP in April 2014 lots of clients are replacing their systems, but some want to upgrade those older XP systems. With 64bit Windows 7 or 8 a performance boost can been seen with 8GB or more of RAM, especially on older systems. They need more memory than Windows XP and extra RAM gets used to buffer disk I/O.This RAM installed easily in the two laptop memory slots and it started right up. After a BIOS warning about how the memory size had changed since the last boot (just press F1 to clear the warning) it worked perfectly.The system has Windows 7 Pro 64 bit installed now and has new life with a new OS.Crucial is the last US Memory maker and I have used their products for years in my own system and my clients. Out of hundreds of memory modules I've installed from Crucial there have been only one failure and the warranty replacement was quick and painless. They cross shipped the part saving time.So my experience with this 8GB kit is consistent with the 5 star quality I've come to expect from Crucial.Hope this helps someone."]

Product: CORSAIR CMZ16GX3M2A1600C9 Vengeance Desktop Memory, 8GB Kit, 2 count,16GB Kit (2 x 8GB)
Reviews: ['Mon i7 de 10 ans a retrouv√© une seconde jeunesse!', 'Le ho prese per velocizzare un vecchi PC con Ubuntu radfoppunandoli la RAM e hanno funzionato perfettamente.', 'Excellente fonctionnalit√©, rapidit√© surprenante, je recommande.', "I bought this ram to replace my old Gskill 4x4gb 16gb DDR3 1866mhz set I had. Two of the sticks started to produce errors and I couldn't send it in for warranty since I lost my receipt.This ram worked out of the box with my AsRock Z77 Professional-M motherboard. By default it was set to DDR3 1333mhz 1.5v's. I had to manually set it to its rated DDR3 1600mhz. It wasn't an issue. I never had ram that was set to its rated speed since my old DDR 400 set from 2004 lol.The ram heatsinks really do an excellent job at cooling the ram, but they are huge! So if you are using a massive cooler like the Noctua D14, you might run into clearance problems.The only con about this ram is it's X.M.P profile. I don't know if its my motherboard reading it wrong or what, but its X.M.P profile sets the ram to DDR3 1556. Even CPU-Z reads its X.M.P profile as DDR3 1556. It's not that big of a deal since I was able to easily manually set the correct speeds, voltage, and timings, but it is weird.So beware, if you buy this kit, you might have to set the correct settings yourself.Overall, this is a great kit. No errors, fast, and the quality of the ram seems to be fantastic. I highly recommend it.", 'Identique que mes originaux, Bon pour augmenter la m√©moire de mon pc', 'Faz o pretendido.', "Corsair CMZ16GX3M2A1600C9 Vengeance 16GB (2x8GB) DDR3 1600 Mhz CL9 XMP Performance Desktop Memory Kit Black\nGreat performing RAM that has overclocked nicely in my system - bought 4 x 8 GB and is doing very well at a bit over 1.5 v along with my Intel Core i5 4690K (at a 26% overclock @ 4,3 GHZ) on an Asus  Z97-A 1150 ATX motherboard with out of the box cooling.I tend to find that it is not a proper substitute for a comb 'though and having teeth at either end rather than along the whole length is clearly a design fault. Also not very convenient to use - and I find that having to remove it from my motherboard to comb my hair every morning is something of a drag. I might buy another module to keep in my bathroom for this purpose and to overcome this issue.", 'Alles l√§uft schnell und sauer. Habe die selben Speicher schon 4 Jahre im Rechner2x4 und mit den neuen 2x8 auf 24 aufger√ºstet es l√§uft alles problemlos. Flaschenhals ( zu wenig Speicher)gefunden und beseitigt üëç', "This is what I had in my system:Motherboard: ASUS SABERTOOTH Z77CPU: Intel i7-3770K, 3.5 GHz, 8MB Cache, LGA1155, 77WMemory: Corsair CMZ8GX3M2A1600C9 Vengeance 8GB (2x4GB) DDR3 1600 MHz (PC3 12800)It worked well, except when I tried to run an virtual machine.Sometimes things would hang.I just didn't have enough memory.So I purchased this memory:Corsair CMZ16GX3M2A1600C9 Vengeance 16GB (2x8GB) DDR3 1600 MHz (PC3 12800)ASIN: B0085IWXB8After communicating with ASUS I put it in these memory slots along with my old 4 GB modules.DIMM_A1: 8 GBDIMM_A2: 4 GBDIMM_B1: 8 GBDIMM_B2: 4 GBNow I have 24 GB of memory and things work a little better.No more hangs running a Virtual Machine.Very happy with it.", "Bought these to replace my defective 8GB (2x4GB) DIMMs that came with my computer. Loaded easily and works well. Only one word of caution/note:By default this RAM seems to operate at 1333 MHz. You have to go into your BIOS and enabled the Intel XMP profile to get it to run at 1600 MHz. Seems kind of weird since 1600 MHz is the default for most (if not all) Haswell-capable motherboards. Wish i could leave 4.5 stars as it's a relatively minor thing, but I suppose if you don't know to look for it you won't realize that its running at a lower speed.P.S. If you are buying this for use in an AMD-capable motherboard, I have no idea how your experience with the memory speed will go.Overall, very glad i purchased this!"]

Product: A Course in In-Memory Data Management: The Inner Mechanics of In-Memory Databases
Reviews: ['Ich habe mir dieses Buch als Begleitmaterial zum Online-Seminar "In-Memory Data Management" gekauft, welches √ºber die OpenHPI Plattform des Hasso Plattner Instituts angeboten wird.R√ºckwirkend bin ich doch ziemlich entt√§uscht dar√ºber, dass das Buch nahezu inhaltsgleich ist mit den seminarbegleitend bereitgestellten und w√∂chentlich √ºber die Plattform freigegebenen kostenlosen Kursmaterialien.
